AROUND 6PM SHE NOTIFIED THE PHARMACIST ON DUTY. SHE STATED TO ME THIS TYPE OF REACTION OCCURS WHEN SHE EATS GLUTEN OR MSG. WE CHECKED THE VACCINE INGREDIENTS AND DIDN'T FIND SUCH IN MODERNA.  SHE WAS THEN GIVEN A 50MG BENADRYL BY THE PHARMACIST. AFTER 10 MINUTES SHE SAID SHE STARTED TO FEEL BETTER.  ALL OF A SUDDEN HER CHEST STARTED TO FEEL HEAVY WHICH SHE WAS BELIEVED TO BE FROM ALL THE EXTRA PHELGM PRODUCTION. WE CONTINUED TO WATCH AND WAIT. AROUND 6:30PM SHE AGAIN SAID SHE  FELT WELL ENOUGH TO GO HOME.  I OFFERED HER AN EPI PEN. SHE DELCLINED. SHE WAS GIVEN 50MG BENDARYL TO TAKE HOME JUST IN CASE.  STATED SHE WAS OK TO GO HOME AND DIDN'T NEEDED ANY FURTHER ASSISTANCE FROM ME OR 911. I  CALLED  THIS AM 2-14-21 TO CHECK IN ON HER. SHE STATED THE RASH/FLUSHING RESOLVED LAST NIGHT AND SHE WAS MUCH BETTER TODAY. THE ONLY SYMPTOM SHE HAD TODAY WAS A SORE ARM.
OTHER_MEDS: EMGALITY, NURTEC AS NEEDED , TRAMADOL AS NEEDED  PROMETHAZINE AS NEEDED, MULTIVITMAIN, THYROID COMPLEX OTC

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I got vaccinated at 11:30am.  Approximately 9 hours after vaccination (~8:30pm), I started to feel lethargic.  9.5 hours post-vaccination (9pm) my face started feeling warm; my temperature was around 99 and I developed a mild headache.  At 10 hours post (9:30pm)  I had chills and my temperature continued to climb (~101F).  At 12 hours post-vaccination my temperature was 102.2, which is the highest it was that I know of.  This was during the night and I woke up several times due to my fever and chills; my headache worsened and was very severe.  I was extremely lethargic and had trouble getting out of bed.   I did not take any over the counter medications.  The following morning my temperature started coming down and my chills resolved.  My headache has improved but is still present (mild).  At around 19 hours post vaccination (~6am) my temperature was 101.  And 24 hours post-vaccination it was 100.5.
I had extreme vaginal itching.  I used anti-itch cream, coconut milk soap to the area, and also took baking soda baths.

I got the second does of the Pfizer. I had a massive headache and chills overnight. I had a fever of 100.1 at 7.10am the next morning. I was leaving my ground floor bathroom and I woke up on my basement floor. I fainted and fell down a flight of stairs. I passed out again, when I tried to get back up the stairs. I crawled back up the stairs and phoned my husband to come home, He did and helped me into the bathroom to wash my teeth. I fainted again and he caught me and carried me back into the sofa. I spent the rest of the day in bed. I am bruised and scraped all over. I am sore all over. I went to Urgent Care on 2/13/21 and got x-rays done.  I have a fracture in my right thumb and may have a dislocated left shoulder. I have to see more doctors tomorrow. I sill don't fell well and I have no appetite. I fell really weak.  I have dizziness when lying down, that may be related to the fall.
LAB_DATA: 4 X-rays and blood work. Follow up appointment tomorrow.
OTHER_MEDS: Remicade, Imuran, Levothyroxine, Prempro. Vitamin B and D, L-Glutathione & Theanine.

6 pm 2/10 I started experiencing severe chest pain. I went to the ER for the pain (no cardiac history). They did all the cardiac tests which were negative and administered morphine for the pain (not effective) and then fentanyl which was effective. I was admitted overnight and discharged at 2pm the following day (2/11). The attending cardiologist could find no explanation other than the vaccine. Although I felt fairly good in the morning (the pain had subsided after the fentanyl administration the previous night) I was tired and went to bed when I got home.  Almost immediately severe chills started with violent shaking for several hours, followed by vomiting large amounts three or four times. About 7pm when I attempted to get out of bed to use the bathroom, I fell on the floor as I could not support myself. I was unable to get myself up due to extreme muscle weakness. My wife had to call my stepson to come over to help get me back into bed. A couple of hours later I tried to get out of bed very carefully and at that point I was able to stand with no problem. There then were no further symptoms other than headache. The following day (2/12) I felt much better but spent the day in bed. 2/13 I was up much of the day but still felt somewhat weak and tired. 2/14 (today) I am still much better but somewhat tired with slight malaise.
LAB_DATA: 2/10 Chest x-ray, ct scan 2/11 Echo cardiogram

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Mild to moderate flu like symptoms first 3-4 days, dryness, metallic taste in mouth. Thought I was in the clear but day 7 I started with periodic PVCs that progressively got worse and more frequent. By day 14 I was having series of PVCs every 5-10 minutes along with changes in bowels and chills (ie autonomic dysfunction) since I have dysautonomia I made an appointment with my cardiologist  and an NAET acupuncture appointment. Acupuncture eliminated the autonomic issues and reduced the PVCs by 90%. I still followed up with cardiologist who was ble to confirm PVCs via auscultation and EKG.  He advised me since acupuncture helped to proceed with second dose and if PVCs worsened again he would do a echo and halter monitor.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I am due September 12, 2021. At the time of the first dose, I was five weeks and three days pregnant. I went to bed early that night (7:30 pm) but attributed it to pregnancy.  I awoke at 3:00 am on 2/11/2021 with a headache, fever, nausea and pain and swelling at the injection site.  My temperature was 100.4. I ate some crackers and went back to bed until 6:00 am.  At 6:00 am, I still had a slight fever (100.4) and the nausea was still there.  I had some toast.  At 7:20, I vomited.  I went back to bed around 9:00 am and slept until noon.  When I awoke at noon, my fever had broken (99.6) but I had an intense headache centering around my left eye and upper neck/base of my head on the left side.  This headache has been continuous up to the time of writing this (4 days post second dose 2/14/2021).  Additionally, I have had an increase in nausea and vomiting.  On Friday, 2/12, nausea was constant throughout the day, and I vomited 7 times (5 of them happening in the morning between 5:00 am - 10:30 am).  On Saturday 2/13, the nausea subsided slightly and I vomited only twice.  Now, Sunday, 2/14, there is still nausea (vomiting once) and the headache.  My injection site is no longer swollen, but is still slightly red and has some bruising.

At 3:30 PM on February 12, 2021, after receiving the Moderna second dose at 10:45 AM, I developed a very bad headache and overwhelming fatigue.  The headache worsened, and by 4:30 was throbbing.  Around that same time, I developed muscle aches in both arms, shoulders, back and knees, not unlike the onset of flu.  My temperature, normally 96.7, , was rising through the evening to 97.3, 97., 97.6, and 97.9 during the evening.   I was nauseous and had lost my appetite.  My temperature was rising and by 7:30 was 98.  I went to bed at 7:30 and woke up at 11:00 PM.  My heart was pounding, the backs of both of my arms were hot to the touch.  I checked my smartwatch and my heart rate was elevated to 110-120 bmp sustained.  My resting heart rate is normally 60-70.  I was short of breath and had shaking chills.   I woke my husband and asked him to help me - I was scared.  My heart rate remained very elevated through the rest of the night and well into the following day but the shortness of breath subsided.  It did not come down below 90 until the later afternoon of February 13, 2021.  The headache did not resolve until Sunday morning, February 14.  I am still quite tired and a little achy, but all other symptoms have resolved.  I considered going to the ER but decided it was an expected reaction to the  vaccine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I got the vaccine at around 10:15 am on Tuesday 2/2/2021. I felt fine until that evening. I started feeling pain on my left arm, spreading to my left upper chest and shoulder, spreading to my head on the left side. I went to bed. Woke at about 4:00 am by pain. By then the pain was pervasive, hurting me from head to toe, on both sides. My stomach had sharp waves of pain, eventually my upper right abdomen was likewise in pain. I thought it was my small intestines but it could have been other organs in there such as liver and kidney. I have never felt pain in that area like that before. I got up to pee and drink water. It was painful to move. My right lower back was in sharp pain as I moved. My leg muscles and tendons had sharp pain when I walked. I got back in bed. Lying down eased the pain some. By morning the pain was less severe. I got up again and it was still painful to walk. My leg muscles hurt and my ankles hurt. I ate a yam with some plain nonfat yogurt. The pain became worse all over. I got back in bed. The pain eased a little, but did not ease as much as earlier in the morning. Eventually the pain moved down to my uterus, then by noon it moved to my inner thighs. By 1:00 pm it was in my knees as well. There?s still pain everywhere but the more severe pain was moving down to my lower body. The pain was disabling. I feel it more when I got out of bed. It?s aching pain mixed with sharp pain, like pulling a muscle kind of sharp. I?m afraid to eat because it seems like the pain got worse after I ate. Had a glass of milk at 4:00 pm and it made me feel worse. Did not eat or take my supplements the night of 2/3/2021. Cleaned up the kitchen despite the pain because I had to. Lied on the couch and fell asleep. Woke at 9:30 pm and went to bed. Still achy all over but pain less severe. Pain in knees and below continued. Woke 6:30 am 2/4/2021. Pain was much less severe when I woke. Went downstairs to take my thyroid meds and felt sharp pain on my left leg mostly calf and ankle as I walked down the stairs. Went back to bed and pain came up to my left thigh and groin. Becoming more and more pronounced in my left groin. It?s sharper and higher up and closer to my uterus. By 7:30 am the pain was up to my left armpit. My left leg was feeling a little numb. On the whole the aches are less pronounced and the traveling sharp pain less frequent. Staying in bed was still the best way to deal with the pain. I started feeling hungry but it?s only been an hour and a half since I took my meds. Waited two hours to have plain nonfat yogurt with banana and pears. Felt okay afterwards. Was able to do a zoom session. Had a large bowel movement. Felt okay. There?s still lingering pain on left side, but less severe. The milder pain lasted through the rest of the day. By afternoon there?s sharp pain in right labia minora. Felt like an open sore. Pain was intermittent. Was able to prepare and eat light dinner. Fell asleep on the couch. Woke at about 11:00 pm with strong frozen muscle pain digestive on left side. Sat up and drank 2 large mugs of warm water slowly. Pain finally passed two hours later. Labia minora intermittent sharp pain continued. Examined area with hand mirror but found no open sore. Found nothing. Washed area with hand held shower. Felt no open sore when examined by hand. No sharp pain felt in area upon touching and washing. Skin felt smooth and intact with no break. After washing the sharp pain was gone. Went to bed and it?s only slight pain on left calf and ankle now. Slept till 7:00 am. 2/5/2021. Fairly pain free except upper left arm of shot area still sore. All day fairly pain free. At bedtime a splitting pressure headache on left side developed and became more and more severe. Pain was sharp. Lasted about an hour. The sharpness faded but felt the remnants of lingering pain for longer. Slept till 7:00 am. All day fairly pain free. Headache and leg shoulder blade pain at bedtime. Residual pain felt daily until the 8th day after the shot.
OTHER_MEDS: Levothroid, glucosamine, calcium, B complex, lysine
HISTORY: Cutaneous T cell Lymphoma, Graves Disease
ALLERGIES: sulphur based meds, ampicillin, amoxicillin, nitrofurantoin, bee sting, hot pepper, durian, slight allergy to mango and pineapple

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I got the vaccine at about 9:30 am.  I started to have a headache that didn't totally go away with ibuprofen at 2:00 pm. At 6:00pm I started to get a fever with aches and chills. The aches felt worse than normal flu aches and pains. The aches and fever were on and off for the next day and a half. They didn't fully stop till almost 48hrs after administration. The highest my fever ever got was the second night at 101.9 degrees (F) axillary.

Initially had only soreness and a little fatigue. One week later on 2/13 the area on my arm where I was injected started itching badly. When I scratched it the whole are turned red and large lump about 3 inches long and an inch wide developed. It became painful and hot. Today, 2/14, I still have the lump, redness, and heat covering a spot about 3 inches wide and 5 inches long. This could be a normal reaction, but it seems odd that it would start after a week when the initial soreness had been gone for several days.

I received my vaccine, sat in a chair facing the clock and noted it said 5:00pm.  Within a minute I notice tingling and slight numbness of my soft palate.  I found this odd, but didn't notice any swelling or difficulty breathing.  At 5:02 I texted my husband to make sure my Epipen was in the glove compartment in case I needed it later after leaving the vaccination clinic.  Over the next few minutes the numbness increased and started to spread to my oropharynx area.  I noticed my heart beating faster and wondered if my body was subconsciously anxious about the numb feeling even though I didn't feel worried because I was breathing fine.  Very suddenly my heart started to pound very hard, my entire laryngopharynx went numb and I felt like a deck of cards was sitting in the back of my throat.  I looked at the clock, it was 5:07.  I started to feel dizzy and weak, my heart felt like it was about to explode, my hands were suddenly cold, clammy and shaking, I started to get sharp stomach pains similar to other anaphylactic events, but still no effects on my breathing. I looked at the clock, 5:09, I knew I had to tell someone before I couldn't get up to walk.  As I started to talk to a staff member I felt very disoriented and suddenly went from feeling like I was going to faint to very hypertensive with pain shooting into my left arm.  The staff quickly tooth my BP and HR, I noted my BP was 166/100 (I am normally 114/72) and the doctor stated I was too tachycardic and needed to go to the ER.  At the ER I received Benadryl, Pepcid and an IV, but never needed any epinephrine.  The medications resolved numbness and stomach pain.  I left with the feeling of a tight turtleneck around my throat and it continues to come and go.  Every 6-8 hours I have had to take Benadry and a steroid to keep the intense itching numb feeling in my soft palate away.  I still have tightness around my neck that returns every 6-8 hours, but still no airway or edema issue.  I felt like I had anaphylaxis without the edema.
LAB_DATA: BP was 166/100, HR was tachycardic, O2 sat 96
CUR_ILL: Hypersensitive allergies ever since 1st vaccine, getting intense itching at night requiring Benadryl randomly and chronic migraine
HISTORY: Chronic migraine, hx of asthma, hx of allergies, myofacial pain syndrome.
ALLERGIES: Severe anaphylactic shellfish allergy, Severe anaphylactic bee venom allergy, multiple food and environmental allergies (non-anaphylactic)

The patient indicated that several hours after receiving her vaccine, she experienced pronounced dyspnea and tachycardia. The patient mentioned that, at one point, she nearly passed out while showering from not being able to catch her breath. The patient reported that she contacted her PCP for guidance, who instructed her to visit the ER for a thorough workup; however, the patient stated she did not follow these orders due to concerns of having a high copay. When speaking with her today, the patient assured me that her symptoms have since resolved.

He reported no other signs/sx at the time. He was advised to seek immediate medical attention since wife was with him, he's ~5 min from local hospital, and no other severe sx were currently present. It looks and feels like poison ivy (to which I am very allergic), but >I have not been outdoors or in contact with anything unusual< (and certainly my face has not) - and as an initial precaution, when the first patch appeared, I scrubbed down thoroughly with tecnu and rinsed, followed by mild dish detergent & water, followed by water, followed by Caladryl  (I am an old hand at this).   This would normally shut  down my allergic response even to direct contact with urushiol (e.g., from poison ivy while gardening).   In this case, no.
LAB_DATA: It's Sunday. I will try to see someone tomorrow, as the hives are spreading  despite my taking every precaution not to touch, scratch, etc anything. It's definitely an allergic response -- and the only unusual thing that has happened over the past several days in the vaccine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I had the sho, the second, one,  in the evening and I was fine. It also started from nowhere as I was watching TV at the time. I took a Tylenol and went to bed. Next morning I was fine and felt wonderful. I am a physician myself and it was really surprising for me. The arm had no pain, nothing at all, but the chills were disturbing. I am fine and happy now. SYMPTOM_TEXT: This was NOT an "Adverse" event, but a completely unexpected positive neurological.  This may or may not be related to the second vaccination on 02Feb2021, however this positive event should be tracked.  My mother is 89 years old, and has significantly diminished cognitive abilities.  However 4 days following her second vaccination, 06Feb2021, she became very lucid, her cognitive abilities including memory, was like it was 10-12 years ago, including speed of thinking, responses to questions, she said it was as if she had awoken from having a stroke and recovered.  Her cognitive state does appear to have declined from 06Feb2021, but remains significantly better than prior to that date.  There is no explanation that I know of, no changes in medications, no changes in living conditions.  The question I have is if there was a shift in her immune state (I have extensive immunology background) due to the vaccination that temporarily effected her brain, I have no other explanation.  Again, for elderly people with senility, I believe this type of event should be noted and tracked.  Or is there a researcher who would be interested in this "positive" event that I can communicate with?
ALLERGIES: no med, food, other product allergies known.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine EUA  - I received my second dose IM in my left arm at 9:16 a.m. on Friday, February 12, 2021.  Within a couple of hours, I experienced soreness at the vaccination site (as I was expecting based on information provided by Department of  Health and Human Services).  By about 7:00 p.m. I began experiencing some of the expected side-effects (achy shoulder, arm, neck, ribs, and eyeballs).  I took an Aleve (NSAID) for the pain at about 9:00 p.m.  I felt a little better in the morning on Saturday, February 13, 2021.  I took my second (and last) Aleve at about 7:00 a.m. that same morning and then slept for a few hours longer.  By the afternoon on Saturday, February 13, 2021 most of the previously described symptoms had subsided.  When I woke up at around 3:00 a.m. on Sunday, February 14 , 2021 I woke up with a painful (pain level 7/10) sore throat (mostly on the R side of my throat ), noticed that I had a small blister on the left side of my lower lip, and had what looks like oral thrush or ?COVID-19 tongue?, (bumpy white patches on the tongue).  I slept poorly until about 3:00 p.m.  and was still experiencing these 3 oral syptoms at 5:30 p.m. on Sunday, February 14, 2021 (about 56 hours after receiving Moderna dose #2).

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 7 days post vaccination (a Sunday) I felt achey, tired, toxic. I went to bed for a couple of hours. That night intense muscular and joint aches woke me from sleep. However, I realised it was a reaction to the shot and not an isolated incident when I emerged from a hot shower Tuesday  and found a huge bright red blotch covering the entire top of my left arm, around the injection site. The arm was not sore, but it looked seriously inflamed. Note: I did have an initial  reaction to the shot; the standard sore arm and body aches for 24 hours right after the injection. The reaction I had a week later was similar but much stronger.
LAB_DATA: I took a COVID test Monday (Feb 8) thinking I may have developed the disease in spite of  having received the first vaccine of Moderna one week prior. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Directly after receiving the shot he became pale, dizzy and faint almost passing out. They explained it as Vasovagal syncope reaction. The nurse sad. After some water and the nurse checking vitals he was sitting up and communicating normally so the nurse left to get his discharge entered and shut the door. What happened next happened within seconds then minutes. He was talking about wanting to go to a store and drinking water then said he was nauseous. I asked if he needrd the waste basket and out his water down. By the time I turned back around he was as white as a sheet and going to fall off the exam table. I grabbed him to hold him up and his legs and arms began bending oddly then went limp, his eyes rolled back and began fluttering, his head flopped back and he turned completely blue and making gargling sounds. I held his head up with my thumb in his mouth because I thought he might be seizing abd he wasn't breathing. I was screaming his name and trying to keep him from falling off the table while rubbing his chest roughly to keep him from completely loosing conciousness. I had to keep screaming Hello!!!!  stay awake! Hello! Hello! Help stay awake!!!! They all came in and got him laid back and he stopped gargling and looking around. They took his blood pressure and checked his sugar. His color started coming back and they had him stay about another 30 minutes. They had him walk around before we could leave.  We live a 25 minute drive from the office and I was terrified the entire way that it was going to happen again on the highway in snow. No child should experience anything like that to prevent later illness. No parent should have to witness their child in that state. I thought he was dying. My baby boy was blue...blue! Drilling and gasping. I'm supposed to accept that is a side effect? That is something that happens? No! I  stopped vaccines with my 3 children as babies for this exact reason. This was proof of my fear and my choice as 100% correct. I only chose to get him the HPV Vaccine because Cancer Runs heavily in my family and I let my fear choose. Never again.

Awakened with L superolateral chest pain radiating to L inframammary region in anterior axillary line on post-vaccination  day 3 (Moderna dose #2).  Pt presented for care on post-vaccination day 4.  Pleuritic chest pain, 4-5/10, accompanied by lightheadedness and dyspnea on exertion.  Chest wall locally tender, but pt also on ocp and with positive D-dimer and mildly elevated BNP, so chest CT angio obtained to evaluate for PE.  Symptoms ongoing at time of discharge but treated with OTC analgesics. ***Concern here is (as noted in CT read) raised by interpreting radiologist not just for this patient, but for women with chest wall adenopathy in addition to axillary lymphadenopathy may be difficult to distinguish from malignancy on screening mammography and may lead to increased numbers of biopsies following this screening study if done within a few weeks of COVID-19 vaccination.
LAB_DATA: Normal EKG & CXR.  D-dimer 0.73, BNP 176, hs-CRP 31.9.  Undetectable troponin. CT chest angiography read:  1.  No CT evidence of pulmonary embolus. 2.  ABNORMAL: Left-sided axillary and chest wall lymphadenopathy. Differential considerations may include reactivity to a infectious/inflammatory process (possibly related to a recent left-sided COVID vaccination) versus malignant lymphadenopathy. No left-sided breast mass is visualized via CT. Recommend clinical correlation with physical exam and history for signs/symptoms of the same. Even if there is a suggestive clinical history, such as a recent left-sided COVID vaccination, this finding needs to be followed clinically until resolution to exclude an underlying malignant process. Ultrasound and/or tissue sampling are available for further evaluation as indicated.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient presented on 1/24 with acute onset weakness and numbness of the left leg so a stroke alert was activated. NIHSS 3. Head Ct and CTA head/neck were unremarkable. Not a candidate for tPA given on Eliquis. Initial exam was notable for weakness and sensory loss in the left leg, but a sensory level was also found to the umbilicus raising concern for a myelitis. Of note, the patient also reported that certain red colored things she looked at appeared black. Labs unrevealing- CBC, CMP unremarkable. ESR, CRP normal. UA and UCx positive for E. Coli UTI, she was treated with ceftriaxone. MRIs were done of her brain, cervical and thoracic spine which were unrevealing. On 1/25, her exam worsened including worsening weakness in the left leg and new numbness and paresthesias in the right leg. Reflexes were preserved. MRI L spine was done which was unrevealing. Lumbar puncture was done which showed 2 nucleated cells and mildly elevated protein at 50, but was otherwise unrevealing. IgG Index normal. No oligoclonal bands. She developed mild hyperreflexia in the left leg and continued to have a sensory level, now at around T5-6. Repeat imaging of her cervical and thoracic spine were completed on 1/28 which showed a contrast enhancing hyperintensity at T5. I reached out to the contact tracing center at hospital to find out if this was a reported side effect of the vaccine. The symptoms continued throughout the weekend and I was unable to work. My next workday was Tuesday and I was still short of breath so I reached back out to the contact tracing center who sent me to be tested for COVID. The results came back negative. I contacted my PCP who ordered a chest X-ray and had me get a pulse ox. My heart rate would go up to 138 with one flight of stairs. Sitting eating dinner my heart rate would sit at 108. Brushing my teeth my heart rate was 119.   Thursday, 2/11 - I woke up for my chest X-ray and was light-headed. I put on my pulse ox and my SpO2 was 87%. I went for my chest X-ray and then went straight to the ED. I was hypertensive and tachycardic when I arrived. My blood work and imaging were all normal.  2/12 - I saw a cardiologist who put me on a beta-blocker to temporarily control my symptoms. He believes I am having a secondary reaction to the vaccines as opposed to a primary issue with the heart. I am scheduled for an echo on 2/15 to cover all bases.  Symptoms have NOT subsided to date - I am still short of breath, have chest pressure, palpitations and tachycardia are being controlled with a beta-blocker (resting HR is 60s but will jump to high 90s with any movement), blood pressure being controlled with beta-blocker.   **I was evaluated for palpitations in 2018 but they were found to be minor and no specific cause was to be found, nor was the cardiologist concerned at the time. SYMPTOM_TEXT: This is a 37 y.o. woman who developed an episode of acute self-limited hemolysis just over a week following her second injection of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine.  She has been treated with ciprofloxacin and phenazopyridine immediately prior to the episode for a urinary tract infection.  She had no history of hemolysis prior to this episode.  She was in her usual state of health and received COVID-19 vaccines on 12/24 and 1/14 with the Pfizer vaccine and had no serious side effects at that time.  She then developed dysuria and was seen by telehleath by her primary care physician who prescribed ciprofloxacin and phenazopyridine for her for 3 days ending 1/22.  She took these and her dysuria resolved, however the day after developed what appeared to be blood in her urine.  Then in the following 2 days which were a weekend this worsened and she started feeling poorly.  She also noted that she appeared yellow.  On Monday 1/25 her boyfriend took her to urgent care and she was subsequently sent to an ER at the hospital that referred her to our hospital.  There she was evaluated for gross hematuria with no evidence of urinary bleeding and found to be anemic due to hemolysis.  Her hemoglobin was in the 5's and she received 2 units of PRBCs.  She was transferred here to Medical Center for further management.  After the initial transfusion she did not require blood transfusion and her hemoglobin continued to increase until it was 10.4 on 2/1 which was the day of discharge.  At a follow up appointment on 2/8/2021 she was recovering and feeling well.   Her jaundice had resolved.   No treatment was given from the hemolysis aside from the blood transfusion and it was self-limited.  It is most likely that her acute hemolysis was due to the phenazopyridine as this agent is known to cause hemolysis and she took it for 3 days prior to the onset of hemolysis.  She has no prior history of drug induced hemolysis and had not taken this medication previously.  As this occurred just over a week following her second vaccination I cannot exclude that is could be related to the vaccine.
LAB_DATA: While admitted she had an extensive evaluation including DAT which was negative and testing for PNH, and peripheral blood flow cytometry which was negative.  Her peripheral smear was reviewed with no schistocytes.  G6PD was sent and high in the setting of active hemolysis and transfusion.  B12, folate, and iron studies were normal.  DAT (-) work up was sent to lab and resulted as negative.  Below is her hemoglobin trend and dates from our hospital.  Results from the referring hospital are no available in detail.   1/27/2021 17:53 - 7.4 g/dL 1/27/2021 17:53 - 7.5 g/dL 1/27/2021 23:36 - 7.3 g/dL 1/27/2021 23:41 - 7.3 g/dL 1/28/2021 12:13 - 8.2 g/dL 1/28/2021 18:24 - 8.3 g/dL 1/28/2021 23:51 - 8.1 g/dL 1/29/2021 04:55 - 8.1 g/dL 1/29/2021 17:26 - 8.8 g/dL 1/30/2021 03:52 - 9.1 g/dL 1/30/2021 17:28 - 9.3 g/dL 1/31/2021 05:18 - 9.7 g/dL 2/1/2021 04:52 - 10.4 g/dL

Concomitant medications reported included dupilumab, montelukast, budesonide / formoterol, cetirizine, albuterol and epinephrine.  On 29 Dec 2020, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 025J20A) intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 26 Jan 2021, prior to the onset of events, the patient received their second of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 028L20A) intramuscularly in the left deltoid for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 26 Jan 2021, after receiving the second dose of the vaccine, the patient reported soreness of the arm for 3 to 4 days.  On 30 Jan 2021, the patient presented to the hospital with acute onset of left sided chest pain. The physician reported that the patient developed myocarditis. Consent for Safety to follow up was received.  Treatment for the events, as reported, included patient's concomitant medications of dupilumab, montelukast, budesonide / formoterol, cetirizine and albuterol. No additional treatment information was provided.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported.   The event, soreness of the arm, was resolved on unknown date. The event acute onset of chest pain and myocarditis was not resolved at the time of this report.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 20 year old male with medical history of multiple allergies, who was hospitalized with serious unexpected events of chest pain and myocarditis and a non-serious unexpected event of pain in extremity.  The chest pain and myocarditis occurred 33 days after first dose and 4 days after last dose of mRNA-1273.  Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of mRNA-1273 and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: feeling much worse; Bloodwork with elevated parameters (troponins); Couldn't take food; Couldn't get up from bed; Fever (101�F); Atrial fibrillation; Pericarditis; A spontaneous report was received from a non-healthcare professional concerning a 67-year-old, female patient who developed a fever of 101 degrees Fahrenheit, feeling much worse, couldn't take food, couldn't get up from bed, bloodwork with elevated troponin, pericarditis, and atrial fibrillation.    The patient's medical history was not provided. Concomitant products known to have been used by the patient, within two weeks prior to the event, included Pentasa, metformin, insulin, Zoloft and atorvastatin.  The patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (lot number 028L20A) on 20 Jan 2021 in the right arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.  The patient developed a fever on 25 Jan 2021, and it got up to 101 degrees Fahrenheit on 26 Jan 2021.  On 26 Jan 2021 she felt must worse, couldn't take food, and couldn't get up from bed. On 27 Jan 2021, she was taken to the emergency room where her oxygen saturation was low, but the fever was gone.  She was placed on oxygen, and blood work had elevated troponin. The patient was diagnosed with pericarditis and she was kept overnight. On 28 Jan 2021 she had atrial fibrillation and the medical team couldn't convert her chemically.  She was stabilized on 30 Jan 2021 and she was feeling much better.   Treatments of these events included oxygen and ibuprofen.    The events, fever of 101 degrees Fahrenheit, feeling much worse, couldn't take food, couldn't get up from bed, bloodwork with elevated troponin, pericarditis, and atrial fibrillation were considered Recovering.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 67 year old female who experienced serious unexpected events of feeling abnormal, decreased appetite, bedridden, elevated troponin, pericarditis, and atrial fibrillation, and a serious expected event of fever. The events began 6 days after first dose of mRNA-1273. Treatment with ibuprofen. Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of mRNA-1273 and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: sixth nerve palsy of the right eye; A spontaneous report was received from a healthcare professional concerning a 73-year-old female patient, who received Moderna's COVID-19 Vaccine (mRNA-1273) and developed sixth nerve palsy of the right eye.    The patient's medical history was not provided. Concomitant product use was not provided.  On an unknown date, approximately two weeks prior to the onset of the event, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 01 FEB 2021, she was seen at an ophthalmologist office and diagnosed with sixth nerve palsy of the right eye. An MRI was performed on an unknown date for the patient's condition which revealed there was mild generalized cerebral atrophy, prominent enlargement of the lateral and 3rd ventricles out of proportion to degree of cerebral atrophy. 4th ventricle is non dilated. There is patchy bilateral cerebral white matter flares. Hyperintensity is noted likely representing findings of chronic microvascular ischemic change. No obstructive lesion identified. No contiguous band of flare/T2 hyperintensity along the surface of the ventricles to suggest the presence of transependymal CSF flow. Impression was that in the setting of potential 6th nerve palsy, this constellation of findings may potentially represent underlying increased intracranial pressure. Normal pressure hydrocephalus was an alternative consideration in the appropriate clinical context. No treatment information was provided.   Action taken with second dose of mRNA-1273 in response to the event was not reported.   The outcome of the event, developed sixth nerve palsy of the right eye, was not reported.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 73 year old, female patient who experienced a serious event of Ophthalmoplegia after receiving second dose of mRNA-1273 (Lot# unknown). Very limited information regarding this event has been provided at this time.  Further information has been requested.
LAB_DATA: Test Name: MRI; Result Unstructured Data: Cerebral atrophy with 6th nerve palsy.
HISTORY: Medical History/Concurrent Conditions: No adverse event (No reported medical history.)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Diabetic Ketoacidosis (nausea, heavy breath, could not form words, PH dropping); Increase of resting heart rate 114 to 120 to 130 and max 150; Terrible Migraine; Extreme nausea; A spontaneous report  was received from a consumer, concerning her son, who is 27-year-old, male patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 Vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced diabetic ketoacidosis (DKA), terrible migraine, nausea, heavy breathing and increased heart rate.  The patient's medical history, as provided by the reporter, included Asperger syndrome and Diabetes. No concomitant products were reported.  On 14 Jan 2021, one day prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Batch number: unknown) intramuscularly for the prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.  On 15 Jan 2021, at 10:30 AM, the patient had terrible migraine and extreme nausea. He experienced DKA as he could hardly breath and breathing was heavy. At 6 PM, as stated by the reporter, the patient went to the emergency room and tests were done which confirmed DKA. The patient stayed there for 2 hours but his PH level was decreasing, couldn't form words and heart rate was 150 beats per minute(bpm) and was transferred to bigger hospital where he stayed in ICU. He was discharged in the afternoon on 17 Jan 2021.  On 20 Jan 2021, the reporter stated that the patient again went back into DKA and was sent to hospital.  On 23 Jan 2021, all symptoms were resolved, and the patient was discharged.  No treatment information was provided.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported.  The outcome of events, diabetic ketoacidosis (DKA), terrible migraine, nausea, heavy breathing and increased heart rate, were considered resolved on 23 Jan 2021.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: couldn't move her face and all the left side of her body/ Drooping Face/ Bell's Palsy; couldn't move her face and all the left side of her body; palm went numb; hip pain; lower leg pain; heart racing; really low blood pressure; arm was itching, her whole body was itching; Tongue and roof of the mouth numb; really bad headache; rash on both arms; nausea; vomiting; freezing; chills; Severe allergic reaction/Allergic symptoms; diarrhea; low grade fever; A spontaneous report was received from a healthcare professional who is a 43-year-old, female patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and couldn't move her face and all the left side of her body, her palm went numb, headache, body aches, chills, had a low-grade fever, diarrhea, arm pain, arm itched, whole body itching, rash on both arms, nausea, really bad headache, vomiting, freezing, low blood pressure, hip pain and lower leg pain and a bad headache.  The patient's medical history included helicobacter pylori, two cervical spinal fusions, allergies to shellfish, strawberry leaves and dust. No concomitant product use was reported.  On 26 Dec 2020, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 039K20-A) in the left arm intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 23 Jan 2021, the patient received their second of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 013L20A) in the right arm intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 26 Dec 2020, approximately 20 minutes after receiving the Moderna COVID-19 vaccine, the patient reported she experienced a headache, body aches, chills, had a low-grade fever, diarrhea and arm pain. The headache and arm pain resolved after 4 days.   On 23 Jan 2021, after the patient received her second dose of the Moderna COVID-19 vaccine, she reported her arm itched, then had whole body itched, a rash on both arms, was nauseated with a bad headache and vomiting. Afterwards, she went to school and it "was downhill from there". 5 days of persistent symptoms including sweating, muscle pain, joint pain and left hand swelling. It was further reported that she had to wait 15 minutes and then she drove home which is about a 35-minute drive. So about 45 mins after receiving the vaccine, she noticed her tongue, it was more on the right side of her tongue, she can't explain the sensation. She couldn't really taste. At about the end of her workday, around 15:30 she was finishing the Cdrink off and she said to herself "oh that taste like a regular drink again". This tongue sensation/lack of taste resolved. A 35-year-old male received the first dose of bnt162b2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE, lot number: EJ1686 and expiry date unknown), intramuscular on 30Dec2020 16:00 at a single dose on the left arm for COVID-19 immunization. Patient has no medical history. The patient's concomitant medications were not reported. The patient was not diagnosed with COVID-19 prior to vaccination. Patient has not been tested for COVID-19 since the vaccination. Patient has no known allergies. Patient did not receive any other vaccines within 4 weeks prior to the COVID vaccine. The most recent COVID-19 vaccine was administered at the hospital. Patient received the second dose on 21Jan2021 16:00 (lot number: EL1283) intramuscular on the left arm. After the second dose in left arm, after about 24 to 48 hours, vesicular pruritic erythematous patches in multiple locations of my left arm, left arm pit, left upper back, left chest occured, peaking on day three and still remain after ond week. The blisters have opened leaving behind painful ulcers. This is not a rash that disappears in a few days. It will take much longer than that to heal. There was no rash with the first dose. Also, with both doses, patient had severe elevation of blood pressure as high as 180/100 within 2 to 5 hours on 30Dec2020, requiring about 3 doses of clonidine over 7 days where blood pressure would cycle up and down. Patient has no history of allergic reactions to any medications in the past or other vaccines in childhood. Otherwise, young healthy male with no history of hypertension. The adverse event resulted in doctor or other healthcare professional office/clinic visit. Patient was recovering from the event. Event reported as non-serious.; Sender's Comments: Based on the compatible temporal association, there was a reasonable possibility that the vaccination with BNT162B2 played a contributory role in triggering the onset of blood pressure increased. reddened area with bruising with nodule; reddened area with bruising with nodule; numbness and tingling in right thumb; numbness and tingling in right thumb; EKG abnormal; large bruise on right buttock/right thigh/right arm; Chest discomfort; Heart attack; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable nurse (patient). A 53-year-old female patient received the first dose of BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 MRNA VACCINE), via an unspecified route of administration in the left arm, on 06Jan2021 (at the age of 53-years-old) at a single dose for COVID-19 immunization. The patient had no medical history or concomitant medications. The patient experienced electrocardiogram (EKG) abnormal and large bruise on right buttock/right thigh/right arm on 08Jan2021; numbness and tingling in right thumb on 10Jan2021; reddened area with bruising with nodule on 26Jan2021; chest discomfort and heart attack in Jan2021. The clinical course was reported as follows: Two days later after vaccination, she noticed bruising on various parts of body. The first bruise she noticed on the 08Jan2021. It was probably about 3.5 inches in length 2 inches in width. The patient stated that it did not necessarily have a shape. She had a large bruise on her right buttock. Two days later, she noticed a similar in size bruise on the front of her right thigh. Then a couple days later, she noticed three quarter size bruises on her right arm (two on the inner part of arm, and one on the outer, both on upper arm). The very next day, she developed the same sizing bruise. It was about the same size on her left upper arm. There were no other side effects besides the bruising. There was no itching or redness, no skin, respiratory, or neurological issues. The day before her second dose, on 26Jan2021, she noticed a 4 inch reddened area with a two centimeter nodule inside that bruise. The patient stated that the initial bruises began to heal. They are not as dark as they were. They were reported to have started out red and then turned black and blue. The patient also had numbness and tingling in her right thumb. She was having some chest discomfort after the initial vaccination that is still ongoing. The chest discomfort prompted her to go to urgent care on 08Jan2021, where she had an abnormal EKG on 08Jan2021. The patient was told to follow up with a cardiologist. The patient saw the cardiologist on 25Jan2021, where he did an EKG and ECHO. The EKG was abnormal and ECHO with unknown results on 25Jan2021, but the doctor was unable to determine when the heart attack occurred. The cardiologist also ran labs: a troponin to see if anything was acutely going on, and a D Dimer to evaluate her clotting factors; both were negative on 25Jan2021. The cardiologist recommended a computerised tomogram (CT) scan, which was still scheduled at the time of report. The clinical outcome of large bruise on right buttock/right thigh/right arm, chest discomfort, numbness and tingling in right thumb, and reddened area with bruising with nodule was not recovered and of heart attack and EKG abnormal was unknown.  The batch/lot number for the vaccine, BNT162B2, was not provided and will be requested during follow up.; Sender's Comments: Based on the current available information and the plausible drug-event temporal association, a possible contributory role of the suspect product BNT162B2 to the development of reported events cannot be excluded. The impact of this report on the benefit/risk profile of the Pfizer product is evaluated as part of Pfizer procedures for safety evaluation, including the review and analysis of aggregate data for adverse events. Any safety concern identified as part of this review, as well as any appropriate action in response, will be promptly notified to Regulatory Authorities, Ethics Committees and Investigators, as appropriate.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Nerve Damage Symptoms; its achy all on the left side; shoulder pain; Being lower back pain; the pain in shoulder went to the arms, back across to the front of the chest; dull aching pain; she didn't sleep; groggy; The pain in shoulder went to the arms, back across to the front of the chest; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable consumer (patient). A 57-year old female patient received the first dose of BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 MRNA VACCINE lot number EK9231) (at the age of 57-years-old), via an unspecified route of administration on 20Jan2021 as a single dose for covid-19 immunization.  The facility where COVID-19 vaccine was administered was at a hospital and anatomically located on the left arm. The patient medical history included acid reflux She has been good for last 2 months. She was on Pepcid but not anymore; uterine polyp removal in 2019 (reported as 2 years ago) polyps removed from uterine wall, it was done outpatient but they still put her to sleep, but it had took her 2 weeks to get over the reaction of being put to sleep, it was the anesthesia, it wasn't pain, but she was very tired and groggy after. She does not know the name of the Anesthesia or have any Lot or Expiry; receives flu shot every year with no issue. The patient was not taking any concomitant medications. She has had No positive antibody or Covid test prior to the vaccine. She took the first shot last Wednesday 20Jan2021, she had a weird, not the usual reactions like she had read about. She even went to the Nurse Practitioner yesterday because of it. She was told she has nerve damage from the shot and a high immune response to the shot, which is a good thing, but her question is does she take the second shot. The nerve damage started at 10 o clock that night causing shoulder pain, back pain, being lower back pain, because of it she didn't sleep, only 3 hour Thursday night. She's a teacher and even had to miss school on Friday. It is just a constant dull aching pain. She was groggy. Some symptoms were typical. She never ran a fever, the pain in shoulder went to the arms, back across to the front of the chest, she can follow with the hand here, its achy all on the left side. She went to the Nurse Practitioner and she said it sounds like nerve damage. The NP did not do any test, she really just left the office hoping that it would resolve on its own.  Caller states that this is not going away.  She actually read to not even take Tylenol or Advil 2 days prior as it can lessen the effectiveness of the vaccine. That's why she didn't take Tylenol till Friday Afternoon on 22Jan2021. She toughed it out for 2 days. The doctor told her she can take Advil right now. The clinical outcome of the event: Low Back pain recovered; event Nerve damage was recovering; events achy all on the left side, Dull aching pain, shoulder pain, chest pain, Pain in arm, she didn't sleep, groggy unknown. She is scheduled for the second dose on 10Feb2021.

The day after I had my vaccine I was very drained and had a headache.  This was to be expected.  On the second day after I slept 14 hours.   On the third day I woke up at noon and noticed that the right side of my lower cheek just above the jawline was markedly swollen, as well as half of my lower lip. There was no pain; the skin felt a bit numb, but it did itch at times, though not very intensely.  During the night of the third day, my full bottom lip swelled, and cracked open and oozed a clear liquid the thickness of water, though not a lot of it.  The whole lip looked as if it were a water balloon encased in a thin layer of skin.  Also this day I had a mild sore throat, but no other symptoms.   On the fourth day when I awoke, the swelling was all across the lower portion of my face, but was notably worse on the left side.  It looked like a golf ball was in my cheek.  Also the left side of my lips were so swollen I couldn't close my teeth.   In the afternoon, as I was eating biscuits my upper lip swelled enormously.   At this point it was hard to drink liquids as I couldn't make a seal as my lower lip was swollen unevenly. On the fifth day (today) I awoke with my upper lip extremely swollen.  My lower cheeks were still swollen, but not grotesquely so.  I had a tepid cup of coffee and when I finished my upper lip was no longer swollen!  My cheeks remain mildly swollen.  I didn't go into work today as the upper lip was so horrid, I couldn't be seen, but I will return to work tomorrow.   I should add that I tried EVERY conceivable home treatment for this: hot and cold compresses, ibuprofen, gargling salt, benadryl, hydrocortisone cream...nothing had ANY effect.
Nausea, Fever 102, chills, body aches, vomiting, arm soreness, axillary lymph swelling in injected arm, sweating, redness at injection site, headache and fatigue.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: neuropathy; Day 4 after injection, heat sensitivity in hands and feet; tingling in hands/feet; sharp burning needles sensation up arms and legs; Tips of fingers and toes were numb and felt swollen; Tips of fingers and toes were numb and felt swollen; Hands then started peeling, palms became thickened and rough; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable healthcare professional, the patient.  A 65-year-old female patient received BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 MRNA VACCINE) solution for injection intramuscular in the right arm on 22Dec2020 at 08:30 (at the age of 65-years-old) as a single dose for COVID-19 vaccination. The patient was not pregnant at the time of vaccination. Medical history included A-fib (atrial fibrillation), GERD (gastroesophageal reflux disease) and osteoporosis. Concomitant medications included atenolol, calcium, acetylsalicylic acid (ASPIRIN), famotidine (PEPCID) and omeprazole. Past drug history included known allergies: fexofenadine (ALLEGRA) and codeine. The patient did not receive any other vaccine within 4 weeks prior to the vaccine. Prior to the vaccination, the patient was not diagnosed with COVID-19. On 26Dec2020, day 4 after injection, the patient experienced heat sensitivity in hands and feet, followed by tingling in hands > feet, with sharp burning needles sensation up arms and legs. Heat sensitivity continued. Tips of fingers and toes were numb and felt swollen for several days, while neuropathy continued. Hands then started peeling, palms became thickened and rough. For the events neuropathy, heat sensitivity in hands and feet, tingling in hands/feet, burning needles sensation, tips of fingers and toes were numb and felt swollen, and hands then started peeling an emergency room visit and physician office visit was required. Unspecified treatment was provided for the events neuropathy, heat sensitivity in hands and feet, tingling in hands/feet, burning needles sensation, tips of fingers and toes were numb and felt swollen, and hands then started peeling. The outcome of the events neuropathy, heat sensitivity in hands and feet, tingling in hands/feet, burning needles sensation, tips of fingers and toes were numb and felt swollen, and hands then started peeling was recovering. Since the vaccination, the patient has been tested for COVID-19. Nasal Swab on 13Jan2021 was negative and on 19Jan2021 was negative.  The lot number for the vaccine, BNT162B2, was not provided and will be requested during follow up.; Sender's Comments: The information is limited and does not allow a full medical assessment. Considering temporal relationship, a possible contribution role of vaccination with BNT162B2 to the onset of neuropath, cannot be excluded. The case will be reassessed should additional information become available.  The impact of this report on the benefit/risk profile of the Pfizer product is evaluated as part of Pfizer procedures for safety evaluation, including the review and analysis of aggregate data for adverse events. Any safety concern identified as part of this review, as well as any appropriate action in response, will be promptly notified to Regulatory Authorities, Ethics Committees and Investigators, as appropriate.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 2nd COVID-19 vaccination on 02-11-2021.  NO symptoms with 1st vaccination.  I woke up to a fever of 99.8 on 02-12-2021, which gradually escalated to 102 within 2 hours.  It remained at 102 for most of day. Finally came down to 101.1 by around 6:00PM.  My normal body temperature is low- around 97.6.  I also had an odd sensation at the back of my throat- cannot really describe it- sometimes hurt to swallow- but not consistently.  Only felt that symptom the day of 02-12-2021.  The next morning, my temperature was 99.2.  Eventually returning to normal around 3:00 PM that afternoon. I did not take any OTC medications during the course of recovery.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: By 10 pm on the evening of the shot, I had a very red and bumpy rash about 2 inches in diameter and 1 inch in height between by breasts. I have never had a rash there before nor have I ever had anything that looks like this.  By around 2 am, I had soreness in my neck and radiating down the entire left side of  my body.   A crinkle in the sheet hurt and I needed to attempt to smooth it out but it was difficult and painful to move. By 4 am the soreness was much diminished. Around 7 am fever, body aches, and headache started. I attempted to sleep it off but the symptoms got so severe around 12 noon that I took Advil. I continued to sleep through the day. I had no appetite and felt nauseous.  Around 2pm I felt well enough to eat something.  By 6 pm I felt mostly normal with only a slight headache. Through the 2nd day I continued to have the rash and it did not change but did become slightly itchy.  Tiredness continued but I was able to make it through most of the 2nd day without irritation or exhaustion. I did go to bed earlier than normal on the 2nd day. Third day rash is the same but itchiness is intensified.
OTHER_MEDS: B-12, D3,  Woman's One A Day 50+, Biotin

The patient's medical history was not provided. No relevant concomitant medications were reported.   On 05 Jan 2021, prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On unknown date, the patient developed systemic reactions for a couple days with bilateral axillary swelling and pain that got worse and worse. She developed severe dermatitis with skin necrosis.  On 10 Jan 2021, the patient went to urgent care and was given methylprednisolone 50 mg for four days. Her left side especially was swelling and was macerated with stuff all over it. The patient reported that it was draining also. A computerized axial tomography (CAT) scan did not show any abscess; it showed several lymph nodes on left axilla with the largest being 1.5 centimeters (CM), nothing impressive and nothing that explains skin necrosis. Her white blood cell count (WBC) was 18 (units and reference ranges were not provided) and vital signs were stable with no fever. On exam, the only thing the doctor found was a small lymph node in the right axillary area, and the left axillary area was significantly more swollen. The injection site on the left arm has nothing.    On unknown date, the patient was at the hospital and given antibiotics and methylprednisolone.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported.   The outcome of the events, severe dermatitis, skin necrosis, bilateral axillary pain that got worse and worse, bilateral axillary swelling that got worse and worse, left side macerated with stuff all over it and left side-patient reported that it was draining, were not reported.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 34-year-old, female patient, who experienced a serious unexpected event of skin necrosis, non-serious unexpected event of dermatitis, skin maceration, axillary pain, wound secretion, and non-serious expected event of lymphadenopathy. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Initial On Call Documentation 2/5/21 at 20:36:  Patient called after-hours line with complaint of swollen tongue 5 hours after her second Covid vaccine.  She reported initial lip swelling with the first vaccine.  She took Benadryl when she had lip tingling initially this afternoon.  However, now she is noting indentations on her tongue.  Heart rate around 125. Patient with no previous history of allergy and anaphylaxis. No epi-pen in home. Patient is tearful over the phone requesting advice. Discussed with patient that the safest option would be for her to report to urgent care versus ED for further evaluation and potential management for impending anaphylaxis, especially given lack of EpiPen in the home.  Patient voiced understanding and is getting a ride to an urgent care.  Follow Up Message from Patient 2/8/21 at 11:23:  Update: I developed sudden swelling of my tongue on Friday night approx. 4 hours after receiving my second dose of the Moderna vaccine. I spoke to on call Dr. She advised me to go to urgent care if still open or ER. Throat started to tingle on the way their urgent care. I was given a dose of EpiPen, Pepcid, Benadryl, and Solu-Medrol. They wrote prescriptions and recommended following up with you this week. I've been taking prednisone, Benadryl, and Pepcid. Tongue is still a bit swollen, but it has not worsened. I now have two EpiPen's to use if needed.  Follow Up PCP Appt 2/11/21 at 15:46: S/O: Patient had the second COVID 19 vaccine on Friday 2/5 and she premedicated with 10mg of Pepcid 10mg and post medicated with Benadryl 25mg. Later that evening she was resting when she felt some swelling of her tongue.  She called the Dr who was on call and she was advised to go to the urgent care.  She felt some tingling of her throat on the way there.  She had no rash, difficulty breathing, or difficulty swallowing.  She was given Solu-Medrol, Benadryl and Pepcid IV and was given a dose of an Epi-pen.  She took Benadryl for 3 days.  She finished a round of 60mg daily prednisone (for 5 days) yesterday.  She felt jittery on the prednisone and this has persisted but is improving. She continues to have a feeling of chest pressure.  First dose Moderna 025J20A 1/8/21; second dose Moderna 031L20A 2/5/21.  She continues to note some mild swelling of her tongue but is otherwise improved.  She does continue to have some pressure type pain in her chest which is also somewhat improved and more diffuse in nature.  A/P: She is okay to taper off of her Benadryl.  She has an EpiPen should she need it, though I do not anticipate this being necessary.  She should note continued improvement in her symptoms to include the mild swelling that is persistent in her tongue.
CUR_ILL: Chest pain and lip tingling after 1st dose of Moderna COVID vaccine on 1/8/21.

The outcome for the event hemorrhage on the right eye was not reported.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 76-year-old, female, who experienced serious events of Eye haemorrhage after receiving first dose of mRNA-1273. Patient received his second dose of the Pfizer vaccine.  He was accompanied by his daughter.  Per daughter prior to receiving his vaccine he was his "normal" self.  He was sitting in a chair next to the vaccinator.  He did walk in with a walker and minimal assistance from his daughter.  He did have a gait belt on around his waist.     When I came to patient he was looking straight ahead with his left eye open - right eye s/p surgery to his right eye per daughter.  He did not respond to questions asked.  His daughter stated mentally he is normally intact.  His pulse was faint but palpable.  His color was pale with slight dusky skin to hands.  911 was called.  Undetectable blood pressure initially with his faint pulse. Initially his heart rate was 105.  He was shallow breathing.     BP was undetectable sitting - with oxygenation low 80's on room air.  He was lifted to a bed/cart with legs elevated.  He was given supplemental oxygen.  After laying down with legs up he started to look around.  He was able to tell me his name and respond to questions.     His blood pressure was 117/68 with heart rate 55 and oxygenation on 6L nasal cannula 87-88%.     Patient's daughter stated that patient was recently at hospital with low blood pressure and questionable seizure activity.  No obvious seizure activity noted today.   Parametics - updated with patient history and events.  Blood sugar checked at 183.  Patient neurologically improved with ability to state name, his daughters name and his age.     No injury noted.  Dr phoned and updated on patient condition and events.  Patient transported without injury on oxygen.  Two daughters with patient to emergency room.    Pt being evaluated by cardio on admission for sycope/possible seizure. Still admitted

No adverse effects for the first two weeks.  The morning of 2/7/21 he claimed he was not able to sleep the night before.  He was cold, but only wanted something cold to drink.  He was not able to get through his normal morning routine.  By 8 am we was beginning to get confused and weaker.  By 9 am he vomited and was not able to stand up or walk.  The confusion was increasing.  We called 911.  When they arrived he had chills and was agitated.  He did not have a fever at that time.  He was transported to the emergency room.  We were not able to accompany him there, but were told he was confused, agitated and combatant.  His fever was up to 101 degrees.   The started him on antibiotics and began tests.  He tested negative for COVID and the flu.  By that evening they diagnosed him with viral meningitis and admitted him to the hospital.  The next day we were told that they had ruled out viral meningitis as well as other infections.  The infectious disease doctor said that all tests had come back negative, but they were continuing  to give him antibiotics.  A neurologist and cardiologist were called in and they were not able to find anything either.  He did complain of chest pains, but it was determined that it might be heart burn.  They did see a sign of Afib, but test were not conclusive. On Friday, Feb. 12th he was sent home with antibiotics and heart medicines.  The confusion has improved, but he is very weak and not mobile without assistance.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 11:40am - received 2nd Moderna vaccine at Vaccination Superstation 3:00pm - started to feel queasy (this was also felt with first vaccine) 5:00pm - ate dinner 11:00pm, 2:00am, and 6:00am - vomited 7:00am - tried a small piece of toast for breakfast 9:00am - vomited and immediately had to defecate, while on toilet started to feel dizzy, got up to walk to bed and collapsed on my way, blacked out for a few seconds and hit my face on the carpet.  Husband was nearby, he helped me turn over onto my back, I laid there for about 30 minutes resting and then called nurse line who recommended I go to ER.  Arrived at ER around 10am.  While in waiting room at ER, began to feel dizzy, nurse immediately checked BP and it was low, brought me to room to lay down.  Started IV fluids.  Doctor consulted, suggested it was likely a vasovagal syncope episode.    Ran EKG, CT scan, urinalysis, CBC, chest and finger radiographs- all normal.   Received 2 bags of LRS fluids and was able to eat some crackers, discharged around 3pm.  I was tired and nauseous the rest of the day but was able to eat small amounts of bland food.  No further vomiting.  The next day, 2/14, I was still tired and nauseous but ate small meals and rested a lot.  Today, 2/15, feeling stronger but not 100%, still a little bit queasy but better than I've been the last few days.
LAB_DATA: At the ER on 2/13/21, the doctor ordered EKG, CT scan, urinalysis, CBC, chest and finger radiographs- all came back normal.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Before going to bed on 2/11/21 I noticed I had a red raised bump at the injection site that was tender. On the morning of 2/12/21, I awoke feeling achy and lethargic, almost like a hang-over from drinking. As I started to move around and do tasks for my morning I started to get an intense headache, fevers avg. 103+, and began napping intermittently from noon until 5 PM. I still felt achy, but didn?t take anything besides water and ate dark chocolate to help with my headache.  The redness on my arm continued to spread and ache. I went to bed at 9 PM mostly with body aches and my fevers remained consistently around 103. I woke hourly between midnight and 8 AM on 2/13 and around 3:30 AM I noticed my body aches had gone away. My fevers remained and my headache continued to intensify. When I got out of bed around 8 AM I tried to watch TV and cried when the volume turned on since the noise was too harsh for my head. I couldn?t do sounds the rest of the day and had intensifying headaches and neck pain throughout the day. I lost all color in my face and was able to move around but felt miserable. I tried eating my first meal since 2/11, chicken noodle soup and felt nauseous afterwards. I went to bed around 9 PM and slept in 3 hour increments drinking water and sips of Coke Zero each time I woke up. At 6:30 AM on 2/14 I was so fed up with feeling miserable I decided to take 3 Advil 200 mg liquid gels and slept soundly from 6:30 AM-11:30 AM. I awoke feeling refreshed and mostly better. I hadn?t been eating so I tried an orange and felt good enough to do work for a few hours until I felt neck pain and tension around my temples again around 2:30 PM. I took 2 Tylenol 500 mg gel caps and left my house for the first time since 2/11 around 5 PM. The outing went well, but around 9:30 I could Feel pain coming on again so I took 1 200 mg Advil and got ready for bed. The redness on my arm has grown rather large so I drew boarders around it to see if it continues to spread. It is still bright red and tender. I didn?t sleep very soundly but am still feeling intermittent headaches and have to keep up with my nsaid/ Tylenol pain relief to function.

When I got home, about 35-40 minutes after shot was administered I took some Benadryl.  About 1 1/2 hours I felt back to normal.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On Friday evening, 24 hours after my 2nd vaccine, my left arm started to itch. My arm, underarm and left breast was very red, swollen, itchy,  tender to the touch and my arm felt sort of numb and weird.  Prior to feeling that way, I had a headache and the left side of my neck was tight and painful. I put some Benadryl gel and an ice pack on my arm and underarm. The following day it felt a little better but still had redness, swelling and itchiness. On Sunday when I went back to work, I had NP take a look at my arm. She felt I may have developed a cellulitis and prescribed Keflex 500mg QID x 7 days. Today, Monday, 2/15/2021, my arm is still a bit red and feels tight but is much better than it was on Friday and Saturday.
OTHER_MEDS: Fish oil, peppermint leaf herb capsule, Sam-e, multivitamin, "Calm" magnesium supplement, "PowerPak" electrolytes and vitamins and minerals. No prescriptions.
ALLERGIES: Intolerant to gluten and eggplant. NKDA

Patient received 1st dose of Pfizer COVID-19 Vaccine around 3:30 pm on February 13th and was asked to wait 30 minutes for observation due to previous history of anaphylaxis to peanuts and latex.    Around 3:43pm patient stated she felt dizzy and light headed and appeared flushed.    Her blood pressure taken at the onset of symptoms was 146/72 and patient stated she had chest pain (7/10 on pain scale).   She stated she felt the same way when she had previous anaphylaxis so an epipen was administered and 911 was called.   About 10 minutes later there was no improvement so a 2nd epipen was administered and she left with EMT.    We have been unable to reach for follow up.

I received Moderna vaccine. First vaccination - 1/4/21. Second - 2/1/21. No significant reactions to either: no fever, chills, myalgias, fatigue, etc. However, about 1-2 weeks post the first vaccine, I developed mild distal finger joint stiffness and slight pain and swelling. Both hands. R>L. Involving 3rd - 5th fingers. Not symetrical. No other joint pains or spine pain.  There has been slight reddish soft tissue swelling  of distal phalanges  of involved fingers. Nails look normal.  Also, few punctate red spots - sl painful; they look like punctate hemorrhages. No systemic symptoms. Not requiring medication. Findings persistant till now. No involvement of toes. No generalized body rashes. I do not have psoriasis, but these findings are reminiscent of findings one would see with Psoriatic Arthritis. I am an MD (Internist). I thought this may be interesting since it looks to me like a possible immune-mediated reaction. I do have photographs available.
OTHER_MEDS: Atorvastatin. ASA. MVI. Lisinopril. Omeprazole. Sindenafil.
HISTORY: HT. S/P Prostate CA. GERD. S/P CAB.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Woke up with a slightly itchy left arm with slight swelling and an area of redness approximately 2x4 inches.

It wasn't a big deal., but I wanted to share in case more people report the same thing.  The day after I became incredibly cold and turned the color of ash gray. I felt strange for several hours. And my arm was the most sore it has ever been in my whole life for about 4 days.   But-what I wanted to share, is I am a perimenopausal woman, who has been having severe hot flashes for about 8 months. Sometimes 10 an hour, sometimes just 10 a day since I added in some OTC hormone support.  But, I have not had a single hot flash for 18 days, which has not happened in over 7 months.  It was like after being so incredibly cold after the vaccine, something in my body reset. I do not know if this will be permanent, but it has been the best three weeks in a long time. And, I just wanted to put it on record, as other women my age (almost 50) are vaccinated if it improves their menopause symptoms.
OTHER_MEDS: Vitamin C Vitamin E Vitamin D Calcium DIM Estoril cream Progastrin cream

SYMPTOM_TEXT: maternal exposure during breast feeding; rash to face, hands, abdomen/ erythomatous papules; Doctor reported that the rash sample from the mother identified vaccine strain VZV; This spontaneous report was received from a physician and refers to a female, 40-year-old patient. Her medical history included pre-eclampsia, pregnancy, concurrent condition included breast feeding. She was healthy, did not have recent varicella zoster virus (VZV) infection or exposure to herpes zoster, herpes zoster ophthalmicus, chickenpox or shingles. No known drug allergies (NKDA). The patient did not receive any concomitant therapies. On 19-DEC-2020, the patient delivered a female baby with no congenital anomalies. Approximately last menstrual period (LMP) was on 14-MAR-2020 and the date of conception was established as approximately 28-MAR-2020.  On 20-DEC-2020, the patient was vaccinated with varicella virus vaccine live (oka/merck)(VARIVAX) 0.5 ml, in right arm, lot # T020652, upon internal validation was determined to be a valid lot #, expiration date was not reported but established as 16-JUN-2022 (strength and route of administration were not reported) since it was determined during a prenatal screen, that she was not immune to varicella (for prophylaxis). The physician was not sure, if the baby was in close contact or in the room at the time the patient was vaccinated. No rash occurred at the site of injection following the vaccination.  On approximately 09-JAN-2021- 11-JAN-2021, also reported as day 21-23 post-vaccination, the patient (mother) developed a rash (vesicles) to face, hands and abdomen, less than 10 lesions (also reported as less than 50). The rash was also described as erythematous papules, no vesicles (inconsistency). She was afebrile. The baby was breastfeeding at the time the patient had developed a rash, and was switched to formula on an unknown date in January 2021 (reported also as shortly thereafter) (maternal exposure during breast feeding).  It was not specified if the patient was breast feeding before rash. The physician wanted to send viral isolates. Since 11-JAN-2021, the patient had no new lesions (dried up). She did not receive any treatment. On 20-JAN-2021, the sample scab from the patient's abdomen was collected.  The patient was enrolled in the Varicella Zoster Virus Identification Program to identify if VZV was present and if it was present, to identify if it was associated with the wild-type (WT) VZV strain or with the Oka/Merck vaccine strain.  On 19-JAN-2021, the call was made to physician to confirm receiving requested program information. The physician was not sure, if they would send samples to disease control or another lab or if would participate in the Varicella Zoster Virus Identification Program (VZVIP), since the physician would need to discuss further with the manager. The program information was e-mailed to the physician as requested. The physician had additional questions upon receipt of the program information and an additional phone call was made. Upon speaking with the physician during the second call, the reporter stated, that they would like to send samples through the VZVIP. Detailed shipping instructions were provided.  On 20-JAN-2021, a call was made to the physician to help arrange for the shipping of samples. On that day, the specimen sample was collected from the patient's right foot vesicle/lesion. The physician confirmed, that there would be four total samples sent: 3 samples from the baby and 1 lesion scab from the mother's (patient's) abdomen. The call concluded with discussion that all four samples would be picked up by the courier by the end of business.  On 25-JAN-2021 it was confirmed by the physician, that the 3 patient's specimens were sent to the laboratory on 20-JAN-2021. The samples were delivered. The results were still not obtained. Additional information has been requested.  On 31-JAN-2021, a notification was received from the Varicella Zoster Virus Identification Program (VZVIP) laboratory physician and reported that the samples from the patient and the patient's baby arrived to the laboratory on 22-JAN-2021 and on an unspecified date in January 2021 were confirmed as positive for Oka Vaccine Strain. On 01-FEB-2021, the PCR results were reviewed with the patient's physician who confirmed that.  Telephone call on 04-FEB-2021 was made to provide results of the report received from the physician for the PCR analyses processed through the VZVlP for both the patient and the baby. It was informed by other physician, that the patient's scab sample confirmed the presence of varicella-zoster virus and was identified to be Oka vaccine strain. The physician stated, that both mom (patient) and baby were doing well and were scheduled for follow-up visit on 08-FEB-2021. Additional information has been requested. The outcome of the event of erythropapular rash was recovered on an unspecified date in 2021. The outcome of varicella zoster virus DNA test positive was not reported. The causality between the suspect vaccine and the events was not provided.  This is one of the two linked reports of mother and child (the baby's case # 2101USA009684).; Sender's Comments:  US-009507513-2101USA009684:
LAB_DATA: Test Date: 202101; Test Name: VZV Strain Identification PCR; Test Result: Positive

On 28th October 2020, the patient received the 1st dose of Shingrix (intramuscular). On 1st December 2020, 34 days after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced rash, cold sores and burning sensation. The patient was treated with medication unknown (Antipruritic (Unknown)). On an unknown date, the outcome of the rash was recovered/resolved and the outcome of the cold sores and burning sensation were not recovered/not resolved.   It was unknown if the reporter considered the rash, cold sores and burning sensation to be related to Shingrix.  Additional details were provided as follows: The patient had reported the case for herself. The patient received Shingrix shot and had symptoms for 1 day which were nothing major, similar to how she felt after a flu shot. Then within a month after vaccination, the patient developed a rash on her collar bone, she used an anti-itch cream which helped.  The patient also has a bad cold sore which had started blooming around 1st December 2020, and had not gone away. It was burned underneath the cold sore, the patient treats it with releive cream and also kept the area clean. The paient did not have a primary care physician at the time of reporting, she would try to get one around 20th January 2021. The patient takes a low dose of Xanax and reported years ago that Xanax from another pharmaceutical company did not work the same. The reporter mentioned that while taking a statin she threw up for 2 weeks and lost 30 pounds then was hospitalized. The reporter consented to follow-up. This case had been linked with US2020AMR248335, reported by the same reporter.
