The patient's medical history was not provided. No relevant concomitant medications were reported.  On 30 Dec 2020, approximately 1 day prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (lot number 025J20-2A) intramuscularly in the right deltoid for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.  On 31 Dec 2020, the patient was working and experienced syncope and weakness.   On 06 Jan 2021, the patient reported experience twitching of the face beginning on an undisclosed date and she also continued to experience weakness. No treatment information was provided.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported.  The outcome of the event, syncope, was unknown. The events, weakness and twitching of the face, were considered not resolved.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 23-year-old, female, who experienced serious unexpected event of syncope, and non-serious unexpected events of asthenia and muscle twitching. The events of syncope, asthenia occurred 2 days after mRNA-1273 (Lot# 025J20-2A), while the event of muscle twitching occurred on an unspecified date after mRNA-1273 (Lot# 025J20-2A). Treatment details were not provided. Based on temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded. COVID; Pneumonia; acute appendicitis; low grade fever; headache; muscle aches; congestion; under the weather; fatigued; extremely cold and had chills; cough; Redness; arm swelling; Soreness; slight dizziness; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer who was also an approximately 56-year-old female who received Moderna's COVID-19 Vaccine (mRNA-1273) and who experienced dizziness, redness (vaccination site erythema), arm swelling (vaccination site swelling), soreness (vaccination site pain), cough, fatigue, under the weather (malaise), extremely cold and had chills (chills), headache, congestion (lower respiratory tract congestion), muscle aches (myalgia), low grade fever (pyrexia), COVID (COVID-19), pneumonia, and acute appendicitis.  The patient's medical history was not reported. Concomitant product use included lisinopril, ergocalciferol, colecalciferol/ magnesium oxide/ vitamin B1, and ascorbic acid.   On 08 Jan 2021, approximately hours prior to the onset of the symptoms, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Batch number 037C20A) intramuscularly in the left deltoid for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.  On 08 Jan 2021 after receiving the first dose of Moderna COVID-19 vaccine, the patient had slight dizziness, redness, arm swelling and soreness which all went away by 10 Jan 2021.  On 10 Jan 2021 she had one cough which was nothing to be alarmed about.  On 11 Jan 2021 she started to feel fatigued, under the weather, extremely cold and had chills.  On 12 Jan 2021 the patient's workplace had her take a COVID test, which came back positive on 13 Jan 2021.  Additionally, on 12 Jan 2021, the patient started to get a headache, congestion, was still super cold and had the chills and muscle aches.  She went to a respiratory medical doctor who administered a chest x-ray and told the patient it all looked fine.  On 13 Jan 2021, she had a low grade fever of around 100.1 degrees Fahrenheit.  The following Sunday, 17 Jan 2021, the patient had abdominal pain. She went to the emergency department (ED) where they did another chest x-ray and it showed she had pneumonia.  The patient also ended up having an appendectomy (date not reported). Treatment medications included ibuprofen for pain from the surgery and guaifenesin for congestion.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was unknown.  The outcome of the events low grade fever, headache, chills, fatigue, under the weather, congestion, COVID, and pneumonia, was unknown. The outcome, of the events soreness, swelling, redness, cough, and dizziness, was considered recovered/resolved on 10 Jan 2021. The outcome of the event, muscle aches, was considered recovered/resolved on 13 Jan 2021. The outcome of the event, appendicitis, was considered resolved on an undisclosed date.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 56-year-old female with serious unexpected events of abdominal pain, appendicitis, COVID-19, pneumonia and unexpected events of cough, bronchial congestion, malaise, dizziness. Cough onset day 2 after first dose mRNA-1273, with COVID-19 day 5 and hospitalization for pneumonia and appendicitis day 10. Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of some events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: About two hours after receiving the vaccination, I had severe dull pain in my entire  leftarm which received the vaccination.  About 7 hours after the vaccination, I had extreme fatigue and slept for about 2 hours.  I then got up to go to my neighbor's house (please note, it was about 4 degrees, -6 wind chill, outside at the time).   When I got to the house, I stayed outside and smoked a cigarette for about 5 minutes.  Upon going inside, I got extremely light headed, fatigued,  my hearing went to "white noise" and a high pitched ringing, and my vision got blurry.  I then left the house with assistance to head back home.  While outside, despite the intense cold, I was dripping sweat in a matter of seconds.  I continued sweating and experiencing effects akin to what is felt prior to passing out, for about 7-10 minutes.   I then laid down and went to sleep.  Third day, still some soreness in the arm, but only at the injection site.  No more adverse experiences since.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I am a teacher, so thankful to have received my vaccines.  40 years ago, as a young teacher I had a bad reaction to a flu shot and I have never had another one.  I didn't think this vaccine would be similar.  I am not someone who gets very sick often and I don't miss days of teaching for illness. Note that my first vaccine on 1/21 had no effects.  I did not even get a sore arm.  I even sort of bragged about it. The 2nd vaccine on 2/11 seemed fine until I woke up the following morning feeling like I had been hit by a truck.  I yawned for 3 hours straight, but still made it to school and worked and taught 6 online classes.  I took an ibuprofen that morning because I was feeling so odd.  By 3:00 I was driving home (40 minute drive) and I cried uncontrollably the whole way home while my hands and feet were shaking.  Not normal for me. When home I went almost immediately to bed.  I had a slight temperature and was dizzy. I thought I had the chills but it didn't feel like any chills I have had before.  Usually my teeth would chatter and I would feel hot and cold at the same time. The hottest temperature I had was 100.5.  But by 9 I started shaking so profusely that I couldn't pick up the thermometer any more, I couldn't use my phone, or take a sip of water.  I stumbled to the bathroom holding onto things all the way.  My husband was not home, or I imagine he would have called 911 at that point.  I kept shaking a lot through the night and kept praying that it wouldn't happen to my heart.  I fell asleep eventually and dreamed of fish flopping inside me and my neighbors coming over to to see why the bed was knocking against the wall.   Saturday morning I woke up and all the shaking had stopped, but I found I was too weak to get up much.  Today is Monday and I mostly feel normal, except a little dizzy when I move and the top of my head is tender to the touch.
CUR_ILL: Some infection at roots of tooth
PRIOR_VAX: 40 years ago.  Flu shot

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Information provided by patient.  After second COVID vaccine dose on 2/1 at 10:20am, I woke up around 3am on 2/2 with chills and shaking. These chills alternated with sweats - waking up frequently either with chills or sweats. These symptoms ended around 1900 on 2/2.  Also on 2/2, I began getting left flank pain. I thought this was muscular. Throughout 2/2 and 2/3, the flank pain became worse and worse and I realized it may be a kidney stone (I have had a kidney stone before). I left my work shift early on 2/3 to go to the ER at 2100. There, it was a little complicated because I am pregnant and could not receive a CT scan to check for stones. Based on the information gained from ultrasounds and the UA, they decided to treat for pyelonephritis. I left the ER around 0130 on 2/4 and picked up pain medications and 14 days of cefdinir.   I do know this may not be related to the vaccine, but I think we need to report everything in case there are trends.  ER Provider notes as follows: 31 y.o. female who arrived by Home presented to the emergency department for left flank pain that radiates to her left groin. The pain has been present since yesterday and it is sharp in nature. She took tylenol at 7pm this evening, but it did not help with the pain. She is also 12 weeks pregnant. Patient reports that she passed a kidney stone 3.5 years ago. At the time, she was told that she had an additional stone in the left kidney and has been following with urology. She also reports nausea that has improved with Zofran. Denies fever or chills, urinary urgency or frequency, or blood in her urine. Patient had an ultrasound at Hospital two or three weeks ago that showed a viable IUP. This is her third pregnancy. She denies complications with previous pregnancies and reports two prior cesarean sections.  Patient is sitting up in bed, in no acute distress. Vital signs are normal. Patient presents for left flank pain for the past day that radiates into her groin with associated nausea, and she is 12 weeks pregnant. She has a history of a kidney stone three and a half years ago with an additional stone present in the left kidney at the time of diagnosis. Will obtain CBC, CMP, UA, urine culture, POC kidney ultrasound. Given 1L IV NS bolus, IV zofran and IV morphine.   DDx:  Nephrolithiasis versus UTI versus pyelonephritis versus ovarian cyst versus musculoskeletal etiology   On reassessment, UA negative for nitrites and leukocyte esterase but positive for 50-250 bacteria perr hpf. POC kidney ultrasound negative for hydronephrosis and UA negative for blood. POC US showed IUP with FHR in 170s with good fetal movement. POC renal US repeated after 1L IVF without evidence of hydronephrosis. Will treat for asymptomatic bacteriuria in pregnancy with cefdenir for 14 days given concern for early pyelonephritis. Nephrolithiasis is still possible but unlikely cause of symptoms as there is no sign of obstructive uropathy on bedside US. Through shared decision making, will not undergo CT limited high for stone evaluation at this time given risk of radiation to fetus. Will discharge home with plan to follow-up with OB and PCP in 1-2 days - also provided Rx for roxicodone and miralax. Strict return precautions discussed. Patient voices understanding and agreement with plan. Denies further questions at this time.

The event, vision not clear, was considered resolved on 30 Dec 2020. The outcome of the events, pounding of chest, and throat felt contracted were unknown. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Numbness of face, tongue, throat; Tingling of face, tongue, throat; A spontaneous report was received from a health care professional concerning a 60-year old, female patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced numbness and tingling of face, tongue and throat.  The patient's medical history was Rheumatoid arthritis, hypertension and possible allergy to diphenhydramine and meperidine. No relevant concomitant medications were reported.   On 13 Jan 2021 at 10:11 A.M., prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 041L20A) intramuscularly in the right arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 13 Jan 2021 at 10:15 A.M., after receiving the vaccine, patient started to experience numbness and tingling of face, tongue and throat.  Initial examination included lungs angiogram, which indicated regular tachycardia. Findings included swelling of lips and tongue, and uvula midplane, not deviated. The patient was moved on an observation area. Emergency medical services (EMS) were notified. Intramuscular (IM) epinephrine was administered at 10:23 A.M. At 10:25 A.M. the patient's vital signs included blood pressure 185/87, heart rate 128, respiratory rate 20, and oxygen saturation 100%. A second IM epinephrine treatment was given at 10:26 A.M. At 10:29 A.M. the patient's vital signs included blood pressure 185.87, heart rate 134, and oxygen saturation 100%. At 10:29 A.M. treatment included oral diphenhydramine. Next dose of IM epinephrine failed; a fourth dose was given at 10:35 A.M. At 10:45 A.M., EMS arrived, and the patient was taken to the emergency room.  Action taken with the second dose of mRNA-1273 in response to the event was not reported.   The outcome for the events, numbness and tingling of face, tongue and throat was unknown.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 60 year-old, female patient, who experienced events of numbness and tingling of face, tongue and throat. The events occurred within minutes after the first and last dose of mRNA-1273 vaccine administration. Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded and the events are assessed as possibly related.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Periorbital swelling; Generalized facial edema; Oropharyngeal edema; Felt faint; Tingling lip; Facial redness; Appears pale; A spontaneous report was received from a healthcare professional concerning a 56-year-old, female patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced lower lip tingling, pale in color, periorbital and generalized facial edema and facial redness.   The patient's medical history was not provided. No concomitant product use was reported.  On 13 Jan 2021, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 041L20A) in the left arm intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 13 Jan 2021, at 0845, 7 minutes after receiving the Moderna COVID-19 vaccine, the patient arrived for observation at urgent care. The patient stated she felt faint and her lip was starting to "feel swollen" and tingling. Initial vital signs were: blood pressure � 147/79, heart rate � 69, respirations � 20 and oxygen saturation � 99 percent. A nurse practitioner and doctor evaluated the patient and noted patient had oropharyngeal edema and lungs were clear to auscultation (CTA).   At 0851, diphenhydramine 25 milligrams orally was given with no effect. Facial redness and edema worsened.  At 0855, epinephrine 3 milligrams was given with improvement, but after 5 minutes, facial redness and lower lip worsened.   At 0902, a second dose of epinephrine was given.  At 0903, vital signs were: blood pressure � 162/87, heart rate � 104, respirations � 20 and oxygen saturation � 100 percent on 4 liters of oxygen. Facial redness and edema improved but still had swelling and tingling of lower lip.  At 0909, emergency medical services (EMS) were called and patient was transported to emergency room/department.   Treatment for the event included diphenhydramine, epinephrine and oxygen.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not provided.   The outcome of the events, lower lip tingling, pale in color, periorbital and generalized facial edema and facial redness, were considered unknown.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 56-year-old, female patient. The patient's medical history was not provided. The patient experienced serious, unexpected event of periorbital swelling, facial swelling, oropharyngeal edema and unexpected events of Paraesthesia oral, erythema, pallor and dizziness. The events occurred 8 minutes after the first dose of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 041L20A) administration. Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Anaphylactic reaction; A spontaneous report was received from a healthcare professional concerning a 24-year-old, female patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced Anaphylactic reaction.  The patient's medical history included allergy to milk. No concomitant medications were reported.  On 12 Jan 2021, 5 � 10 minutes prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 intramuscularly in an unknown arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. The patient experienced chest tightness and tachycardia symptoms following which she was transported via gurney to the observation area. The patient looked sleepy and had trouble arousing her. The blood pressure was at 140/80 mmHg, heart rate was in the 90s to 100s heartbeats per minute. The patient's breath sound decreased bilaterally. It was also noted that her throat felt uncomfortable. The reporter stated that anaphylaxis reaction was suspected due to the rapid decline in status. Following an increasing heart rate and complaints of chest discomfort the patient was treated with a dose one of epinephrine pen. It was noted after a minute or two the patient's chest felt better. Her blood pressure was stable at 140/80's mmHg, the heart rate initially increased to 110 and then back down to 100 about 5 minutes after the first dose. At about 8 minutes from dose one of epinephrine pen, the patient's heart rate increased to 160 and developed additional symptoms of chest tightness again so a second dose of Epinephrine pen was administered. The patient was somnolent but protecting airway. Oxygen was added 2 liters after second dose of epinephrine pen. The patient's oxygen saturation dropped right around second dose of epinephrine pen to 94% but about 2-3 minutes later it was back at 98%. The paramedics arrived 5 minutes after second dose of epinephrine pen and care was transferred to them. The patient was transported in a stable condition.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not provided.  The outcome for the Anaphylactic reaction was unknown.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 24 year old, female patient, who experienced serious unexpected event of Anaphylactic reaction. The event occurred 1 day (5-10 min) after mRNA-1273 (Lot# Unknown). Treatment included EpiPen (2 doses). Very limited information regarding this event has been provided at this time. Based on temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded. Additional information has been requested.

Patient was at vaccine clinic today for her 2nd dose. She reported to the vaccinator she had a mild reaction with the first dose. Verified with pharmacist we would observe her for an additional 30 minutes as a precaution. She received her vaccination and was sitting in a chair talking with another associate. Associate when she reported she began to feel dizzy, lightheaded, nausea and felt like she might pass out. Patient at this point laid on the floor and put her feet up, a cart was brought to the room and patient was able to get up and climb onto the cart with no difficulty. VSS, respirs easy and non labored. Patient laid on cart supine for approximately 10-15 minutes and then the HOB was elevated aprox 30-40 degrees, she was sitting up on the cart talking with another associate/friend drinking small water bottle provided and eating a bag of chips. She finished the water and stated she felt sick to her stomach, she was offered crackers. She did not appear to be in any respiratory distress at this time. She remained sitting up on the cart resting when she stated she was beginning to feel like she "does when she has a tree nut reaction" she then asked if she could get an "epi shot", we advised she was breathing easy and her oxygen saturation was WNL and did not meet criteria to receive an epi shot. Pt became upset and voiced "this is how I get when I have a reaction and I can breathe fine until I can't". Associate was advised if she felt she might need an epinephrine injection, she should consider being evaluated in the emergency department. She agreed to be transported to the emergency department to be evaluated for a possible reaction to the vaccine. Emergency department was notified of patient, patient was transported by cart to the ED accompanied by RN. report given to ED staff. ED Visit to Hospital Emergency dept: : ED Visit at hospital resulted in patient receiving 2 doses of Epinephrine, solu-medrol and Benadryl.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received my Moderna shot on Saturday 1/23/21 around 4PM. On Tuesday -- 1-26/21 -- AM I woke up with a slight pain on the side of my left foot.  In the middle of the pain there was a small black dot .  I am an unusually healthy 83 y.o. physical active, ex Marine, with a high tolerance to pain.  So at first I paid no attention to this and went and played pickleball that very day.  But the next day I awoke to find that the foot was not only bright red and swollen, but painful.  I immediately called my doctor and the next morning I had a telephone conference with him.  We discussed the possibility of what could have caused this problem.  Although I am pre-diabetic (111) he ruled out diabetes.  He also ruled out gout. This only left the possibility of an infection.  But since I had not stepped on any nails, etc. the only possibility was a bug bite.  So he prescribed an antibiotic, which I started taking that very day.  After several days the foot got progressively worse and turned into a ulgy, oozing sore and redness grew to the whole left side of my foot.  So I made an appointment with my doctor for a physical visit, however this was delayed until 2/5/21.  By then the swelling and redness had subsided considerably and the wound was healing.  He ordered lab tests to rule out the possibility of diabetes and gout.  He also gave me a prescription for stronger antibiotic and antibiotic ointment.  Unfortunately the lab was by appointment only and I did not get the tests done until 2/12/21.I would not even be writing this except for the fact that on 1/27/21 I also developed a rash all over on my back that was very itchy.  This is when my attention turned back to my vaccine shot, and the reports that Maderna had a track record of rashes from their shots.  So I thought I had better write to see if it would be safe for me to get my 2nd Maderna shot which is scheduled in just 6 days (2/20/21).I do have a history of occasional painful rashes since childhood and I am wondering if the Moderna shot could have possibly triggered one, or both, of these problems?  If it will help I did have photos taken of my foot during this episode and will be happy to send them to you if you feel it necessary?Thank you for your immediate consideration and response.
emesis

January 20 received first shot-Moderna 005J20-2A at the hospital.  Arm sore for about a day c. January 22 onward-slight headaches January 26 began having severe chills. These lasted for about 4 days. They were most severe on January 29. Concurrent with chills was the onset of fatigue.  c. January 29-severe pain in hips and shoulders rendering me almost immobile. It was very difficult to get out of bed and to walk. I used a cane for support. Also the onset of diarrhea and loss of appetite. Tried extra strength Tylenol, but it did not help.  Never had a fever, respiratory symptoms, of loss of taste or smell. Had nasal Covid test of February 1 which was negative. Saw Doctor on February 4. He ordered blood tests, one of which was to check potential source of joint pain. The test was negative for that, but showed some lessening of kidney and liver function.  February 8-blood test showed considerable improvement on kidney and liver function. All symptoms except the fatigue have gone away. I did lose about 5 pounds during this reaction period.  The fatigue is improving.

The where the shot there is about a mark on the muscle where I got the shot. On 28th of January, I went to see my doctor, my shoulder was swollen and I could not raise my arm to about my shoulder level. When I try to move I could feel a pain up there. Doctor put ice on it and told me to take Aleve. Since the swelling has went down I am no longer putting ice on it, I am not using heat. I tried to put my arm in  a sling but it is painful. The other pain I feel no pain in my arm is I sit on the couch and put my arm straight out and do not move. The black area on the bicep is almost gone, the darkened area up by my collarbone went away, most of the darkened area is on my left breast. If I rotate my arm counter clockwise or clockwise there is pain there and it feels like it is stretching the muscle. I have also seen Doctor on the 2nd or 4th of this month. I am thinking of going to see him again this week. My doctor thinks that the person who gave me the vaccine, hit a blood vessel and that is what caused the blackness on my arm. The pain is mainly in the collarbone area and in the bicep.   Before this started, about the first of January I came home and  went to put my keys up and went to reach up  and had some pain in my arm, but the pain and mobility issues both went away before receiving the vaccine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient received 0.3 mL of incorrectly diluted or undiluted Pfizer vaccine. When the nurse went to administer another 0.3 mL from the vial to the next patient, she noticed that there was insufficient volume. Only one vaccination was drawn from the affected vial, and that vaccination was given to this patient. Patient had left the facility at the time that the error was discovered, but he was contacted by telephone to be notified that he potentially received an improperly diluted or undiluted dose of Pfizer vaccine. Patient was notified that typical symptoms of immune response after being vaccinated, such as headache, fever, body aches, etc, may be exaggerated. Patient was instructed to use over-the-counter antipyretic acetaminophen according to bottle instructions, as needed for those aforementioned symptoms.

January 7 - I didn't notice anything different. January 8 - things got intense: my right arm when I got to work; it was tingling and I was real shaky. I was administering vaccines that day and I had issues with my hand shaking really bad. I ate chocolate to see if that would help and it didn't go away. A few hours later - I left work at 2:30 - my left arm went numb and started tingling, too. I had a lot of discomfort in my chest and heart area. I didn't feel right. I tried to take a nap - but it felt like impending doom; I had extreme chills but I had no fever - like I was going to have a heart attack. I called my husband. I took an Ativan (I had some that was five years old). I went to sleep. I woke u next morning and felt extremely ill and felt very fatigued. Subjective; Patient is a 38 yo male who was seen at COVID Vaccine Clinic today for his second  dose of the COVID 19 vaccination. He was given the Moderna vaccination in the right deltoid muscle.   During his 15 minute waiting period after the injection, the patient began to experience lightheadedness and diaphoresis, chest tightness that is reproducible by provider with palpation.  He denied difficulty breathing, wheezing, throat tightness and dizziness.   This provider was notified of patient reaction and he was then assessed in the emergency bay area.   Monitored patient for severe reaction symptoms, including but not limited to blood pressure abnormality , rapid progression of symptoms, respiratory distress and vomiting.   During monitoring, patient complains of shortness of breath and chest tightness.  SpO2 100% room air, blood pressure elevated at 152/104 at 0840, 147/112 at 0900.  Patient is alert and oriented.  O2 per NC placed at 0900, SpO2 at 100%.  Patient was able to eat and drink during monitoring.  Blood glucose is 107.  BP at 0910 150/93.  He is not on any prescribed medications. Patient is a 99-year-old man with prostate cancer and sprouting eyes. No signs of dementia; awake, alert, and oriented by 3 (person, place, time). The patient needs a walker and a person assisting so he can move. He visited the pharmacy and came with two family members. After I evaluated the patient, I administered the vaccine. Just after the administration of his first dose of the Covid-19 Vaccine he felt very dizzy and with severe headaches after standing up.   Family members told me the patient occasionally suffers from dizziness when he changes from the sitting position to the standing position.  I sat him again and he keep telling everyone he did not felt fine. He was semi unconscious; his eyes were almost wide shut and his family members besides me told me he felt cold and never had dizziness like this. Just after that, I asked him if he could breathe, and he nodded yes with his head. I was ready for applying CPR or oxygen depending on the scenario.  But I was very worried for him because of his age and decided to call the ambulance. The paramedics came in half an hour, but he started to feel better after a while. The paramedics got his blood pressure and was low and his glucose levels were high. They recommended the patient to go to the hospital, but he refused. He talked with his family members and instead decided to go home.

Patient and her husband are elderly, but healthy and live independently. Patient took blood pressure medicine 'off and on' according to family. She was 5'2", 120 pounds and slim and healthy and active, so was her husband, though he had pulmonary fibrosis so they had been staying home and not attending church etc, and masking when they did go out to protect against covid disease. They were both vaccinated with covid Pfizer vaccine (dose #1) on Thursday Feb 11. (02/11/2021) Thursday night as they went to bed they checked in with each other on how they each felt. Patient said she felt totally fine, and her husband said his arm was a bit sore. Patient woke before her husband on Friday Feb 12, went downstairs and, from what the family can tell, fixed herself a snack, then sat on the sofa. Patient's husband found her deceased on the sofa. He called 911 and they asked him to do CPR until the paramedics arrived. Because of proximity to covid vaccine, the ME wanted to examine the body in the home and also ordered an autopsy. Autopsy was completed on the same day as death, Feb 12, 2021
LAB_DATA: Autopsy ordered by Medical Examiner. Completed on day of death, Friday, Feb 12, 2021 (2/12/21) Findings reported to the family were that she had bleeding in the brain related to hypertension, and "90% of the main coronary artery was occluded" - per family.  ME told family that death was unrelated to vaccine. Family believes this, but agreed to let me report this event in case there is a pattern and this data will help advance science.
OTHER_MEDS: HTN meds taken 'off and on', UNK other medications etc.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Baseball sized diameter swelling around injection site, red (like a rash) in color, itchy, painful to touch and warm to touch. Hip, knee, foot, shoulder and elbow pain on left side only, Body aches,  nausea, visual impairment and loss of balance. Difficulty concentrating and relative "brain fog". Severe drowsiness in the sense of falling asleep while talking to someone and then no memory of it. Chest pressure and constant feeling of being out of breath. Cannot catch breath walking across the house from one room to the next. Severity of symptoms subsided within 24 hours, but some linger up to the time of this report. They are shortness of breath,  rash with warmth and pain, lack of concentration and brain fog. Elbow still tender to touch.
OTHER_MEDS: Vitamin C, Vitamin D, Clonidine, Losartan, Amlodipine, Glimipride
HISTORY: Type 2 Diabetes, High Blood Pressure and high cholesterol.

During her 15-minute waiting period after the injection, the patient began to experience lightheadedness and headache, flushed, left deltoid where vaccination given hot to touch, nausea.  She denied rash, difficulty breathing, lip swelling and tongue swelling.   This provider was notified of patient reaction and she was then assessed in the emergency bay area. SYMPTOM_TEXT: 30 Hours after the shot without any warning or ill effects, I suddenly collapsed from my chair at the dining room table.  Fell on the floor unconscious and ended up in the Emergency room with a broken nose ,concussion, and no memory of the episode.  Hospital did a CAT scan which did not show indication of a stroke but did verify concussion and broken nose.  Later saw personal physician and heart monitor was placed on my body, and echo cardiogram scheduled.  Echo cardiogram did not indicate any blockage.  Results from heart monitor not available at this time.  I am a perfectly healthy individual - walk 3-4 miles every day, swim, play golf, eat a keto diet and have never had an episode like this.  An hour before it oc   Apple watch 6 texted a message that read:  "are you okay or should we call 911".    I was perfectly fine and just thought the message was a fluke - replied I am fine.  An hour later the episode occured.  I am not used to taking vaccines - no flu shots, no shingles shots - only keep up my tetanus.  The only vaccine I have had recently was in 2009 - yellow fever shot so I could travel to.  I have never had a reaction like the one after the Moderna vaccine.

Pt breathing easy and regular.  1230: Pt states itching better, and redness on R ear is getting better. Husband has arrived to be with pt and wait for ambulance. Pt states still itches but still gone from her feet. Redness on ear remains good. Pt talked with husband about concern of taking ambulance. This nurse did state she thought it was safest way for pt to be transported in case anything happened further on the way to the hospital but the patient does have the right to refuse the ambulance.  1240: Pt states itching feels like increasing some. I took 2 extra strength tylenol around 4 pm and 2 more when I went to sleep around 10:30 pm. I felt much better when I woke up on Sunday(no lethargy, didn?t feel feverish) but around 2 pm I noticed a red, blotches rash all around my neck, and my upper torso. There?s was also a rash on  the right side of my upper back. I called my PCP but the office was closed for President?s Day. I didn?t feel that the symptoms warranted going to the ER, but I took 2 25mg tabs of Benadryl at 3 pm. It is now 7 pm and the rash on my neck and upper torso looks unchanged but, I also noticed it had spread to the crook of both elbows Otherwise, still feel fine. Body temperature is 98.9 orally, which is slightly higher than my normal temperature, which tends to be around 98 degrees. I  had a similar, but, much more severe reaction to Ibuprofen about 10 years ago, though it started out in similar fashion and got progressively worse over 3 - 4 days. Hx of severe recurrent acute sinusitis until the age of 40. Being sheltered in place since Apr 2020.  Beginning Jan 2021 I started experiencing a little yellowish nasal discharge with slight nasal congestion and occasional pressure in the maxillary sinuses. On Jan 21 received the 1st dose of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine. Because of no improvement with symptomatic treatment of sinusitis, on Feb 3 started Augmentin 500 mg 3 times a day. On Feb 7, symptoms became much worse: fever 38.2C (100.7F), chills, muscle aches but the most troubling symptom was severe (level 8) face pain. Bouts of pain lasted for a few seconds but repeated about every 30 sec. It felt like an electric shock originated in the nasopharynx and extending to the maxillary sinuses. Pain affected both sides of the face but mostly the right side. Additional symptoms: scalp tenderness, neck pain and light stiffness while moving, skin hyperesthesia. On Feb 8, underwent PCR COVID-19 testing, which was negative.  On Feb 12, canceled the 2nd dose of Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine, rescheduled for Feb 19. Since Feb 14 no pain and fever.  Treatment:  1. Because I had a thought that I may be developed a nasopharyngeal Herpes zoster infection, on Feb 11 I started  Famciclovir 500 mg 3 times a day. 2. Ibuprofen 400 mg 3 times. 3. Augmentin (stopped after 4 days, on Feb 7).

Arthritic pain in the toes, hips, thumb, elbow/ elbow pain/ thumb pain; Soreness in his chest muscle; wrist stiff; Arm began to swell; Limited arm movement; Burning at the injection site; This case was reported by a consumer via and described the occurrence of injection site burning in a 54-year-old male patient who received Herpes zoster (Shingrix) for prophylaxis.   The patient's past medical history included viral arthritis.   On 25th September 2020, the patient received the 1st dose of Shingrix (intramuscular). On 26th September 2020, 1 days after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced injection site burning. On 29th September 2020, the patient experienced swelling arm, mobility decreased and stiff joint. On 9th October 2020, the patient experienced arthritic pains and musculoskeletal chest pain. On an unknown date, the outcome of the injection site burning, swelling arm, arthritic pains and stiff joint were recovered/resolved and the outcome of the mobility decreased was unknown and the outcome of the musculoskeletal chest pain was not recovered/not resolved.   It was unknown if the reporter considered the injection site burning, swelling arm, mobility decreased, arthritic pains, musculoskeletal chest pain and stiff joint to be related to Shingrix.  Additional details were reported as follows: This case was reported by patient for himself. The patient received Shingrix on left arm. SYMPTOM_TEXT: shortness of breath; throat tightness; HR 133/HR 137; diarrhea; hives around injection site; Hives around i njection site and on contralateral arm and chest; flushing sensation; felt anxious; BP 131/87/ BP 131/85/BP 145/76; A spontaneous report was received from a nurse concerning a 34-year-old, female patient who received Moderna's Covid-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced flushing feeling, felt anxiety, blood pressure fluctuation, hives around injection site and contralateral arm and chest, diarrhea, shortness of breath, throat tightness and heart rate abnormal.  The patient's medical history included anxiety and attention deficit hyperactivity disorder. Concomitant product use was not provided.  On 09 Jan 2021, prior to the onset of events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 026L20A) intramuscularly in her arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 09 Jan 2021 at 13:30, immediately after receiving the Moderna COVID-19 vaccine, the patient reported having a flushing sensation and felt anxious. At 13:36 the patient's vital signs included blood pressure 131/87 mmHg, heart rate 99 beats/min, and oxygen saturation 99%. Doctor noted hives around the injection site and on contralateral arm and chest. Patient was moved to a separate room to lie down on a bed; on route to the new room, the patient developed diarrhea. Treatment included diphenhydramine.   At 13:49, the patient reported having shortness of breath and throat tightness. 99%. Intramuscular epinephrine was given and 911 called. The patient's vital signs included heart rate 133 beats/min and oxygen saturation  At 13:55, the patient's vital signs included blood pressure 145/76 mmHg, heart rate 137 beats/min, and oxygen saturation 99%  At 14:00, emergency medical services arrived, and patient was transferred to hospital. Patient left the office in stable condition with vital signs within expected range and fully conscious.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not provided.   The events, flushing feeling, felt anxiety, blood pressure fluctuation, hives around injection site and contralateral arm and chest, diarrhea, shortness of breath, throat tightness and heart rate abnormal, were considered resolved.; Reporter's Comments: A spontaneous report concerns a 34-year-old, female patient who experienced serious events of shortness of breath, throat tightness and heart rate increased and non-serious events of flushing feeling, felt anxiety, blood pressure fluctuation, hives around injection site and contralateral arm and chest and diarrhea. The events occurred on the same day after the administration of the first dose of mRNA 1273 (Lot # 026L20A, expiration date unknown). Treatment administered include diphenhydramine and epinephrine. Outcome is resolved. Based on the information provided, which indicates a strong temporal association of the reported events with the administration of mRNA-1273 vaccine, a causal association cannot be excluded. The event of hives around injection site is consistent with the known safety profile of mRNA 1273 vaccine

SYMPTOM_TEXT: A spontaneous report was received from a consumer concerning a 65-years-old-female patient who experienced her right arm is red, itchy, site of injection was way lower than where it should be given, arm is red, and redness spread down injection site and passed her elbow. On 2/12/21,"almost two weeks after the vaccine was received, I started having sever muscle spasms. They were shooting through the right side of my neck and shoulder. Any sudden movement or wrong movement triggered the spasms.  Even taking too deep of a breath triggered the spasms.  Using my left arm to lift something triggered the spasms. My pain level that day was at a 10+. On Saturday the spasms had subsided, but I  still had very limited ROM in my neck. It felt like my neck muscles had been over worked and my neck felt weak. Pain continued and I went my doctor on Monday 2/15/21. After me explaining to him the course of events and letting him know I did not do anything at all that could have caused an injury,  he felt this was a reaction to the Covid vaccine I had gotten on 2/1/21. He advised me to take my muscle relaxer that he had already prescribed to me and to use a heating pad.  He gave me some exercises to do with my neck and prescribed me Hydrocodone 5-325 mg to take as needed every 8 hours for pain. He told me if it got worse or did not get better to follow-up with him.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On 12 FEB 2021 I received my first dosage of the Moderna COVID 19 Vaccine, Lot 016M20A. On the day of the vaccination, the pain from Psoriatic Arthritis  (primarily bi-lateral feet was low in comparison to the average level of pain over the last 7 days).  There was also discomfort in the hips which for time to time had presented with point pain at the connection of the hip to the Femur. BLUF: Most significant joint/muscoskeletal pain related to exacerbation locations for Psoriatic Arthritis that I have ever endured since receiving the injection.  Prepared for second vaccination, but fearful of PSA not being in control and dramatic escalation in discomfort in feet and hips, affecting ability to walk.  I received my vaccination at some time after 1400 hours, 12 FEB.  No issues noted until approximately 2300 hours, 12 FEB, when significant and debilitating pain was noted in multiple joints or areas affected by recent Psoriatic Arthritis exacerbations.   Initial Pain made it difficult to sleep from the 12th into the 13th due to significant discomfort. Through that first night, the pain immediately flared, bilateral feet, left and right hip and point pain at three locations on veterbrae, (lower, mid and upper back).  Pain was most pronounced in feet and left hip,  the feet (all toes seemed to throb in pain and were sensitive to touch or simple movements).  Pain in feet and left hip was a 10/10.  Left hip pain was slightly different than the point pain and seemed to radiate out from the area where it connects to the femur. 13 FEB: By 0815 on 13 FEB the pain in the right foot and right hip decreased, as well as the pain in the lower, mid and upper back but the pain in the left foot and left hip continued, slightly less strong than the night prior.  Pain level decreased to 8/10 for left foot and hip and was down to a 5/10 for the right foot and hip and a 3/10 for the areas on the back. In the evening of 13 FEB it was noted that the pain in the left hip became more generalize:d vice the specific point pain that I have witnessed off/on since SEP 2020.  Continued to note evening pain that felt like burning/tingling pain on both feet.  At this point the pain in the evenings appeared to be worse than the AM pain.   Left Foot: 9/10 Fight foot: 7/10 Left and right hips generalized pain: 6/10 Lower, mid and upperback: 5/10 It should be noted, that left shoulder discomfort from the injection never exceed 2/10 as it appeared 24 hours after the injection.  More pain in shoulder associated with mobility/rotation? I lacked the ability to simply walk through the house due to the pain throughout the past 36 hours.   14 FEB: Less discomfort in AM, but still greatest in left foot. Left Foot: 7/10 Fight foot: 4/10 Left and right hips generalized pain: 3/10 Lower, mid and upperback: 4/10 PM:  Significant increase in pain at bed time. Left Foot: 9/10 Fight foot: 7/10 Left and right hips generalized pain: 6/10 Lower, mid and upperback: 5/10 15 FEB: AM: continued lessening of pain/discomfort in AM, but appeared back throughout the day, worsening at evening.  Pain in left hip was noted to be much more pronounced shooting out in multiple directions, to include causing discomfort from the rear of the hip, and when seated shooting pain in the direction of my inner thigh from the back of my hip.  Pain in feet continues to be like a burning/tingling pain in the evening, most pronounced in 2nd and 3rd toes on my left foot and big toe and little toe on my right foot.  The pain also appears to be much greater at evening than in AM. Left Foot: 9/10 Fight foot: 7/10 Left and right hips generalized pain: Left Hip 8/10 right hip 6/10 Lower, mid and upperback: 5/10-not much change-very point specific pain.. I am not witnessing fatigue or any other problems other than joint/musco skeletal pain.  I have also not been getting shooting pain in feet that has appeared from time to time which feels like someone hammering nails into individual toes or shots of violent pain, only a sustained burning/tingling pain. four days later the Psoriatic Arthritis locations continue to rage following the vaccine, most notably bilateral feet and left hip, where the pain in the hip appears to be radiating in multiple directions.
OTHER_MEDS: Paused on weekly Enbrel injections since 1 January 2021.  Taking Losartan/HCTZ 100MG daily; St Mary's thistle capsules (for fatty liver); Magnesium; Vitamin D3
CUR_ILL: Active Psoriatic Arthritis primarily bilateral feet.
HISTORY: Psoriasis; Psoriatic Arthritis; High Blood Pressure; Diverticulosis/re-current diverticulitis; Non-Alcoholic Fatty Liver Disease

SYMPTOM_TEXT: It started with tingling in my tongue (which I ignored), then it became numbness that spread down my throat I also became short of breath. That's when I notified one of the nurses. They checked my blood pressure. I vaguely remember hearing it was high (189/?). They called 911 and the paramedics came. Shortness of breath became worse and chest pains started. The paramedic gave me Benadryl and then epinephrine since I was increasingly getting worse. I was shaking  and I felt lethargic. I could not control the shaking and I felt cold. I do not remember a lot of details when I got to the Emergency Room. Looking at my record they gave me: LORazepam (ATIVAN), methylPREDNISolone sod suc(PF)(SOLU-MEDROL) and famotidine. I went home that night with the condition that I see my primary care physician. I felt like I have the flu and soreness of arm the next couple days. I went back to work after four days.

Several days after 1st Covid-19 vaccine I have incidents at least 2 times per day feeling shakiness, feeling like blood sugar was low, feeling weak and dizzy and clammy This lasted for 2 weeks post the 1st vaccine. Also experienced headache for 10 days post vaccine. After dose 2, Flushing on face and chest. Tingling and heaviness on chest. Feeling short of breath and feeling tightness in throat Tingling of arms. BP was 141/101 (normally runs low). I was informed that I was having a panic attack and was released by the staff. Chest tightness, heaviness and difficulty breathing continued. On Saturday 2/13 I went to urgent care and was prescribed an inhaler and steroids for shortness of breath. I continue with feeling heaviness in my chest, difficulty with shortness of breath, and hoarseness in my voice/tightness in my throat especially with increased activity or talking.
CUR_ILL: Slight congestion 2-3 days prior to vaccine. Was seen by PCP and informed that this was probably a common cold. No other symptoms on the day of the vaccination. Was tested for Covid-19 on 1/22 after the 1st vaccine to rule COVID out as a possibility following my adverse reaction to the first dose of the COVID vaccine. My test was negative at that time.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On 2/9/21 I woke up with a raised,  red, swollen rash on my left arm probably 2" x 2" in size.  I had a scratchy throat, mild headache and chills.  I went to Urgent Care (per my primary care's instructions).  Diagnosis was Cellulitis (skin infection caused by bacteria at the injection site) and put on 100mg Doxycycline twice a day for 7 days.  Over the next few days the rash increased in size and I still was getting chills and tingling sensations on my skin especially my face so I contacted my Primary Care and had a follow-up appointment with them on 2/11/21.  I was told to stop the Doxycycline because they did not think it was Cellulitis, but was a reaction to the Vaccine (Covid Arm).  On 2/15/21 I saw my Dermatologist because I am still having tingling sensations on my face and my Rosacea is acting up - they put me on a topical cream Ketoconazole.  The rash on my arm is just a little red at the outer edge, but slowly disappearing.
LAB_DATA: Because of my symptoms on 2/9/21 U was tested fir Covid (nasal swab sent to a lab) results came bac k NEGATIVE on 2/10/21
OTHER_MEDS: Atorvastatin 20mg, Travoprost eye drops, Aspirin 81 md, Vitamin D3
PRIOR_VAX: Tetanus - red rash, hot, hard

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Got First Pfizer Covid vaccine on 06JAN2021. About 4 days after that I started noticing allergy symptoms and mild intermittent wheezing. Then on about the 5th day after, my lower back pain increased, causing significant sciatic pain worse than ever before. On 22JAN21 I ended up going to urgent care for increased breathing problems, and also had to have pain management appointment within days as sciatic pain was debilitating and also significantly interfered with my sleep.  After steroid injection (In spine)on FEB 3rd for sciatica/back pain, and steroids/inhaler treatment for the breathing stuff, I would say I was pretty good to go . I didn't think too much of these unusual events for me both in timing and severity. On 12FEB2021, I got my second pfizer covid dose. I 14FEB I started noticing allergy symptoms again, and slight shortness of breath, used inhaler I had from before to help as breathing in seemed to not give me full breaths. Then, on 15FEB2021, in the evening out of nowhere while walking, my lower back/sciatica pain came back in full force, as if my leg were a lighting rod like before. So it almost seems as if the covid vaccine triggered an inflammatory reaction in my body. I am not certain, but because the series of events seem the same and in timing after my first covid vaccine, I figured I would at least report it.
LAB_DATA: 22JAN21: Chest Xray, CBC and Covid test (Covid test was negative).

Concurrent medical conditions included penicillin allergy.   On 30th November 2020, the patient received the 1st dose of Shingrix (intramuscular). On 30th November 2020, less than a day after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced chills and influenza-like symptoms. On an unknown date, the patient experienced eye red, eye swelling, skin blotches, erythema eyelid, itchy rash and red face. The patient was treated with acetic acid (Apple Cider Vinegar) and antifungals for topical use (Antifungal Cream). On 1st December 2020, the outcome of the chills and influenza-like symptoms were recovered/resolved. On an unknown date, the outcome of the eye red, eye swelling, skin blotches, erythema eyelid and red face were unknown and the outcome of the itchy rash was not recovered/not resolved.   It was unknown if the reporter considered the chills, influenza-like symptoms, eye red, eye swelling, skin blotches, erythema eyelid, itchy rash and red face to be related to Shingrix.  Additional details were provided as follows: The case was reported by the patient herself. The patient reported that, she received the 1st dose of Shingrix and that night she awoke with the worst chills and flu like symptoms ever that lasted one day. Within two days, her left eye was red and raised and then it moved to the right eye.  The patient went to a doctor and they said that it was not consistent with shingles.  The patient had not changed anything prior to getting the rash and within that week she had purchased new mascara and eyeliner.  The patient also experienced a red, blotchy area on her face but it looked different than the red area on her eyelids.  The rash itches in phases and it has crept under the eye (more so on the left eye) and in the corner of her eyes on her right eye.  The patient tried apple cider vinegar which helped a little and she received an antifungal cream that she just received today on the day of reporting. Her eye rash got worse and then spread to both eyes and has slowly resolved somewhat but it was still there.  The patient had a drug allergy to penicillin. The reporter consented to follow up.

Pt was told that we would like her to stay for further evaluation. Pt was talking to husband on phone without difficulty and asking him to move to garage area to pick her up. Previously administered products included Shingrix with an associated reaction of injection site pain (for the tolerance of 1st dose, refer case- US2021AMR004190). Concurrent medical conditions included hashimoto's disease.   On 6th January 2021, the patient received the 2nd dose of Shingrix. On 6th January 2021, less than a day after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced injection site pain. In January 2021, the patient experienced fever, shivering, fatigue, headache and nasal stuffiness. The patient was treated with paracetamol (Tylenol). Rechallenge with Shingrix was positive. On an unknown date, the outcome of the injection site pain was not recovered/not resolved and the outcome of the fever, fatigue, headache and nasal stuffiness were recovering/resolving and the outcome of the shivering was recovered/resolved.   It was unknown if the reporter considered the injection site pain, fever, shivering, fatigue, headache and nasal stuffiness to be related to Shingrix.  Additional information was provided as follows: The patient received 2nd dose and experienced soreness at the injection site in her left arm.  At 1 am, experienced shivering, fever (101 degree celsius), headache, stuffy nose and fatigue. The patient took Tylenol and the symptoms were resolving. The reporter did not consent to follow up. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Vasculitis on her head, at the back of the brain; Horrible pain in the neck; Pain on the back; Feeling dizzy; Motion sickness; Vertigo; Horrible headaches; raging headache; Nausea; awful nausea; feeling tired, fatigue; Sore arm; Body aches; A spontaneous report was received from a 53-year-old, female, patient who was also a physician who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced vasculitis on her head, at the back on the brain, sore arm, feeling tired; fatigue, body aches, awful nausea; nausea all day long, horrible headaches, motion sickness, feeling dizzy, horrible pain in the neck, vertigo, and pain on the back.   There was no medical history provided. There were no concomitant medications reported.  On 24 Dec 2020, the patient received the first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 intramuscularly in the left arm, for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 25 Dec 2020, the patient experienced sore arm, feeling tired, body aches, and fatigue, which continued through Sunday, 26 Dec 2021.   On 27 Dec 2020, she began experiencing awful nausea, horrible headaches, vertigo, and motion sickness in addition to the ones she suffered before.   On 28 Dec 2020, the patient experienced nausea all day long.   On 29 Dec 2020, she went to the emergency room (ER) as she was feeling dizzy, had nausea, and had a raging headache. In the ER, she was given IV fluids, diphenhydramine hydrochloride, and other non-specified medications that helped with her symptoms. The patient went home with prescriptions and the next day she had results from lab work done, which included sedimentation rate was 44 (doubled) and her plaquette count was above normal. Treatment form her primary care physician included steroids, acetylsalicylic acid, meclizine hydrochloride, and prednisone. The patient reported an MRI was done and her physician told her she had vasculitis on her head, at the back on the brain. She was referred to a neurologist and was asked to do more bloodwork.   On 12 Jan 2021, the patient reported she was still experiencing horrible pain in the neck, nausea, vertigo, dizziness, and pain on the back, with symptoms beginning on an undisclosed date.   Action taken with mRNA-1273 to the events was not provided.  The outcome for the events, vasculitis on her head, at the back on the brain, sore arm, feeling tired, fatigue, body aches, horrible headaches, and motion sickness, was unknown. The events, pain in the neck, nausea, vertigo, dizziness, and pain on the back, were considered not resolved.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 53 year old female patient experienced a serious unexpected event of Central nervous system vasculitis and NS events of sore arm, feeling tired; fatigue, body aches, awful nausea; nausea all day long, horrible headaches, motion sickness, feeling dizzy, horrible pain in the neck, vertigo, and pain on the back. The events occurred few days after first dose of the study medication administration. Treatment included IV fluids, diphenhydramine hydrochloride, steroids, acetylsalicylic acid, meclizine hydrochloride and prednisone.  Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

Approx 12 hours after receiving second dose of covid vaccine, I experienced what I can only describe as moderate-strong flu symptoms. I had previously had a mild reaction to the first vaccine (fatigue, mild headache) so I was shocked at how incapacitated I was after the second vaccine. 9:00pm (Wednesday)  (12 hours after vaccine) - after feeling ok all day, starting to feel sick, chills yet feeling hot (fever at 101.4), muscles and joints aching and headache; 9:00pm-4:00am - very intense flu like symptoms, muscle and joint aching extreme, burning and deep pain on arm at injection site, chills not going away.  I eventually fall asleep. 7:00am (Thursday) - call my mother to come pick me up because I am still feeling poorly.  Fever is gone but I have a major headache and body aches are persistent. I take Tylenol and some of the body aches are better. I continue to feel like this throughout the entire day off and on. 7:00am (Friday) - finally feeling better but I have a lingering sense of extreme nausea that won't go away. My stomach itself is "fine" but the nausea is persistent. I take dramamine and feel somewhat better. 7:00am (Saturday) - still feeling fatigued but almost feeling like myself again. Nausea is still present but has greatly diminished. 7:00am (Sunday) - finally feeling mostly "ok" again. No noticeable major effects that are interfering with my ability to go about my day.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I awoke at 3:00 a.m. this morning (Feb 16) with itching in my skin beginning to be felt. By 3:30 am it was widespread and developing a rash over much of my torso and arms. I felt dizzy when standing, and there were waves of mild nausea. I had major nasal congestion and could breathe only through my mouth. My CPAP machine (which I use all night every night) was on before the 3 am wakeup, and I donned it again when I returned to bed at around 4 am. Nasal congestion now has improved a lot. On two occasions  (maybe around 4 am) I noticed a minor wheeze. On a couple of occasions I coughed lightly, and it was a sore one from the chest. I still have some dizziness, and now an intermittent headache. Before going to bed last night I took two Naproxen Sodium PM tablets for some neck pain.

68-year-old female evaluated for painful movement of her extremities. Patient reports that her symptoms started the day after receiving the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine at pharmacy. Patient was admitted. Patient has been evaluated by Neurology, Rheumatology and the Ortho-Spine Service. Symptoms improved with prednisone. Although unclear, a diagnosis of polymyalgia rheumatica was being considered due to elevated CRP (inflammatory marker). Relationship to vaccine administration is also unclear. Pt with Hx of arthritis, COPD, CAD, CHF, and HTN received first dose of Pfizer COVID-19 Vaccine. Within 24 hours of vaccine administration, pt went to hospital c/o of painful movement of extremities. Pt was treated with prednisone and symptoms improved. She was evaluated by multiple specialties including neurology, rheumatology and orthopedics without a clear diagnosis. Her CRP was elevated to 17.2 mg/dL and Sed Rate to greater than 130 mm/hr and reactive ANA titer. Total CK was normal at 23 IU/L. Rheumatology wrote this is highly suggestive of COVID-19 vaccine induced polymyalgia rheumatica which has been reported with other vaccines but not with COVID-19 vaccines.
HISTORY: Asthma/COPD; Coronary artery disease; Hypertension; CHF

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Blacked out; fell down the stairs; concussion; damaged or severed 6th cranial nerve to right eye; brain bleed; split lip; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer concerning a 79-years-old, female patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 Vaccine, and who blacked out, fell down the stairs, brain bleed, concussion, damaged or severed 6th cranial nerve to right eye and split lip.   The patient's medical history included diabetes, two unspecified high blood pressure medications and naproxen sodium. Products known to have been used by the patient, within two weeks prior to the event, included Sitagliptin and blood pressure medication.  On 21 Jan 2021, approximately one and half hours prior to the onset of the symptoms, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number 027L20A) intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.    On 21 Jan 2021, the patient "blacked out" while walking downstairs after one in and half hours of receiving vaccination. Patient was hospitalized from 21 Jan 2021 until 22 Jan 2021. Patient has a brain bleed and a concussion, damaged 6th cranial nerve to right eye, and split her lip which need stitches. Treatment for the event included Tylenol as needed.   Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was withdrawn.   The events blacked out and fell down the stairs was resolved on 21 Jan 2021. The outcome of the events brain bleed, concussion, damaged or severed 6th cranial nerve to right eye and split lip was unknown.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 79 year old female patient with medical history of diabetes, two unspecified high blood pressure medications and naproxen sodium, who experienced serious unexpected events of fall, cerebral hemorrhage, loss of consciousness, concussion, damaged or severed 6th cranial nerve to right eye and split lip. The event occurred approximately one and half hours after first dose of the study medication administration. Treatment included Tylenol as needed.   Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded. Noting the subject's underlying medical condition could remain a confounder.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: delayed reaction; WBC in blood; felt tired; diagnosed with Urinary tract infection; blood in urine; soreness in the arm lasted 24 hours; A regulatory authority report was received from a consumer regarding himself, a patient who is a 68-year-old male patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced soreness in the arm that lasted 24 hours, diagnosed with a urinary tract infection, blood in the urine, WBC in the blood, felt tired as a delayed response to the vaccine.  The patient's medical history was not explicitly provided, however the patient noted that he takes "blood pressure medication" and "Benign Prostatic Hypertrophy medication."  On 12 Jan 2021, prior to the onset of the events, the patient received one of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 013L20A) intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On the same day, patient stated that he had soreness in the arm that lasted 24 hours. No treatment information was reported and event is considered recovered/resolved.   On 13 Jan 2021, after the mRNA-1273 vaccine was given, the patient was reported to have been diagnosed with a urinary tract infection and had blood in his urine.  On 15 January 2021, the patient reported that there were white blood cells in his urine and felt tired. He was questioning if this is a delayed reaction to the vaccine.  Treatment information included antibiotic for the urinary tract infection.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 was not reported.  The outcome of the events, soreness in arm for 24 hours is considered resolved as of 12 Jan 2021. The outcome of the events, urinary tract infection, blood in urine, white blood cells in urine, and feeling tired were not reported.; Reporter's Comments: The events of urinary tract infection, blood in the urine, WBC in the blood is more likely associated with the patient's suspected underlying condition of benign prostatic hypertrophy Hence assessed as unlikely related to mRNA-1273. Fatigue and muscle soreness are temporarily associated with mRNA-1273 use and consistent with the known safety profile of the vaccine. Thus, causal association cannot be excluded.
HISTORY: Medical History/Concurrent Conditions: Benign prostatic hypertrophy

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pt reported feeling symptoms approx 10 minutes after receiving injection. She complained of mild shortness of breath and "itchy throat." She was questioned about having any other symptoms and immediately escorted to the medical attention tent. She was seated, and EMS began evaluation; her vital signs were taken: RR 22, HR 82, BP 156/102, PULSE OX 98%. She then reported an increase in symptoms, as face itching, increased tightness in her throat. Objective symptoms observed by myself and EMS: cough/clearing of the throat, increased SOB/labored breathing, facial erythema, hoarseness. EMS asked for her consent to give her Benadryl and Epinephrine. She repeatedly refused this, and refused any attempt at IV placement. She eventually agreed to IM Benadryl, of which 50mg were administered by EMS. Both EMS and I suggested more than once that she allow us to transfer her to the hospital for further management and preparation in the event that she needs further care. I explained that she was having symptoms of anaphylaxis. She repeatedly refused transfer. She reported a decrease in symptoms, saying she felt well enough to go home. Her objective symptoms observed by myself: continued hoarseness and clearing of the throat. VS were repeated: RR 18, HR 68, BP 160/98, PULSE OX 99%. Airway remained patent and clear. Patient again requested to leave, and agreed to EMS escorting her to her car.
ALLERGIES: Hot dogs, Bactrim, Morphine, bee stings - anaphylaxis; epinephrine pen prescription

SYMPTOM_TEXT: COVID-19 Vaccine EUA: I got the vaccine at 11 am on 2/15/21. There were not immediate adverse effects.  By 3:00PM, my arm was becoming very sore. By 8:00 PM, my right arm was extremely sore and overall body aches ensued as I began to feel weak. By 9:00 PM, I felt the need to get into bed and had chills, a severe headache and pain over my whole body, accompanied by shooting burning sensations down both arms into my palms and fingers. I had not taken any medication for the discomfort up to this point.  As time went on, my pain became excruciating, I never felt this kind of pain in my entire body. I had pain in areas I never felt pain before like my arms, hands and toes.  I also had extreme pain in the back of my neck, both shoulders, both arms, my hips and knees. The pain was so intense and throbbing, my headache was severe at my temples and I had chills.  I did not take my temp, but I am sure I had a fever, although I was not sweating. I could not sleep at all and finally broke down at 1:30 am and took an Advil.  There was minimal help with the Advil and I slept on and off over the next 4 hours. Throughout today, the headache, chills and pain continued, but slightly less and I was able to take a 2 hour nap.  I think it important to note that I had more of a reaction to the first COVID shot that most others I talked with and felt an ongoing weakness after the first shot over the course of the month.  I understand that some of my symptoms are part of my body's reaction to building antibodies, but  with the intensity of my reaction, I have to wonder if there is more going on.
Only air was administered,  no vaccine was given. No adverse event was reported.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: After receiving the second shot at approximately 1030AM, I returned home and felt fairly normal. In the evening, I started to feel very weak and developed a fever of 101.9 and took 500mg tylenol and continued to hydrate with water and powerade. Throughout the evening, I checked my temperature, it ranged from 101.9-102.8. I also developed strong chills, which caused me to shiver to the point where my significant other thought I may be seizing. (this also happened with the first shot - fevers and chills). I went to bed, waking up 3 hours later and I had to change my pajamas as I was soaked in sweat. I became nauseous and vomited a decent amount of what appeared to be red blood - but did not want to go to the ER as I was cold and exhausted and extremely feverish. Throughout the next 36 hours I continued to run a fever and struggled to do basic household chores (wash a dish, walk up and down the stairs, change shirts, etc) without assistance - normally not things I would need help with. Having had COVID nearly 90 days ago, the aftermath of the vaccination was worse than the actual illness for me.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On Wednesday, February 3, I received my first COVID vaccination shot, as a medical volunteer at a clinic.   After about three or four days, I had sensation on my left hip that felt like my skin was tingling/burning. Last Thursday, February 11, I began noticing rash like bumps in my pubic area. I thought at first that it was a chaffed place from running. But the bumps continued to spread, including at the base of my spine and my left buttock. And all of the rash is only on my left side. (Oddly, the same side that I received the COVID vaccine shot.) The bumps look like those of poison ivy. But it hurt rather than itched.   Last Saturday and Sunday, (February 13 and 14), it was at its worst, and hurt even to sit down.  Monday, Feb. 15 and Tuesday Feb 16, the rash was still prevalent, but swelling was down  but still feels uncomfortable. I am hoping that it is getting better. It appears to have very similar symptoms to shingles, but I have had both the old shingles vaccine, and both doses of the newer one. My second dose of the new shingles shot was on March 9 of last year, right before the lockdown.
LAB_DATA: No medical tests or labs given, but I did consult with my primary care physician.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I developed a splotchy red rash on the front of my right shoulder, down the center of my chest, and on the left side of my left breast. I did not have any rash on my right arm at the injection site. It looked like a moderate sunburn. It did not itch or bother me in any way., but was warm to the touch.  Each of the three splotches is approximately the size of my palm. At the time that I first noticed the rash, my temperature was up to 100.1. The previous day, my temperature had gone as high as 101.0, but came down after taking Tylenol. I had stopped the Tylenol on the morning of February 15, thinking the fever was over. But by 7:30 PM, my temperature was going back up again, and that is when I noticed the rash. As of 4 PM on February 16, the rash is definitely paler, but still there. In addition, another splotch developed on the right side of my back, again, the size of my palm. I contacted the urgent care center where I was vaccinated, who told me I could come in to have it looked at, but they were about to close. They offered the option of a Tele visit, but no one called me back within two hours. By that time, the rash had started to fade, so I canceled the Tele visit. I took another dose of extra strength Tylenol the morning of February 16. I have not taken another dose since then, and the rash has not gotten any worse. My fever has not returned.

Patient's left arm appeared red & warm to touch. Although it did not appear inundated and lacked tracking, I encouraged patient to contact her primary care doctor's office for evaluation. Patient followed my recommendation and I consulted with the provider. The conclusion was made that patient appears to be having an immune response to the vaccine yet. Dr also consulted with RN (immunizations)  and she reported this reaction has not been uncommon 5 dose post-vaccination. Within 15 minutes of receiving the vaccine, I was dizzy, nauseous, and elevated BP (140?s/90?s). After about 30 minutes, these symptoms subsided. At 1:30 AM on 2/13, I woke from sleep with severe epigastric pain, chest pain, and pain between my shoulder blades. My arm (where I received the vaccine) was throbbing and I had severe under arm pain on the same side. Symptoms lessened with 2 extra strength Tums, 500 mg Tylenol, and 30 mL of Pepto, but were still present. I was able to sleep, I woke up later in the morning with these persistent symptoms, as well as fatigue. All of these symptoms continued for 24h. On 2/14, I had lessened arm pain and fatigue but continued to have epigastric/chest/back pain. I was seen at the urgent care near me and my physical was normal, they indicated that the chest symptoms were likely from epigastric pain since I was not having shortness of breath. I?ve continued to have these seemingly random chest pains and back pains, they?re very intense throbbing sharp pains in my chest and back that do not always coincide with exercise or stress.
LAB_DATA: I have reached out to a cardiologist, I am awaiting a call back to schedule an appointment/ECHO.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Awoke at 1:34 AM and my left foot hurt.  I had a marble-size lump and a few small lumps on the vertical bone above my heel that were tender to the touch. I got up, ate, and in the afternoon after research, I realized it was gout and I had tophi for the first time ever.  I had my first gout flare in November 2003 without tophi, and never had another flare until 2/14/2021!  I walked and suddenly my Achilles? tendon hurt and my heel hurt a little.   I took 2 Colchicine and took one more an hour later.  It seemed much better and didn?t hurt but some of the pain returned.  I couldn?t sleep until 4:05 AM and awoke around 6 according to my Fitbit watch.  I contacted my doctor and he said to take one Colchicine every day until the pain is gone.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: patient received covid vaccine.  screening questions answered.  administered vaccine at 1321pm.  patient wheeled to vaccine waiting room.  patient became lethargic and blacked out.  patient not alert and awake for approximately 1 minute.  patient came to, pulse 80, blood pressure 93/70, oxygen saturation 98%, husband at side, emergency cart and AED and oxygen brought to location of the patient. oxygen 2L nasal canula placed on patient. EMS called and Dr. came to site.  assessment obtained with Dr. at site.  patient awake, was able to speak full name but stated she was not aware of where she was.  this reaction happened approximately 6 minutes post immunization.  within approximately 3 minutes of episode where she states she felt she was going to "black out" she began to shake/ full body involvement.  during this episode patient was following nurse commands.  momements were rhythmic and lasted approximately 10 seconds then stopped.  Patient brought back to exam room.  at 138pm- temp 97.5, blood pressure 144/31, pulse 51, respiration 18. patient stated she felt warm and reports she felt she was going to black out.  this episode lasted approximately 3 seconds and patient became alert at that time.  vitals at 140 pm- blood pressure 124/60, pulse 75, respirations 16.  vitals at 144pm- blood pressure 119/75, pulse 75, respirations 16.  patient has dialysis 4 times a week for CKD stage 5.  patient has lengthy medical history.  patient reports her primary care doctor is Dr. who sees her frequently.  patient reports she has an issue with internal bleeding with source unknown and at times has to have blood transfusions.  no recent illnesses reported.  patient states she ate breakfast around 10am today.  patient states she has never had a vaccine reaction int he past or reaction to needles.  EMS arrived on site approximately 1345.  report given to EMS.  patient alert with EMT.  patient transferred from her personal wheelchair to EMS cot.  patients husband left with patient to go to Medical Center.  Patient tolerated vaccine well immediately after immunization.  She reported no pain at injection site.  Paper tape and 2x2 gauze placed at injection site due to allergy to tape.  Allergy list was reviewed prior to administration of vaccine.  Patient alert and oriented prior to vaccine to person place and time.  Husband present in room.  Verbal consent obtained by patient to receive covid vaccine today .  Vaccine information handout and emergency use handout given to patient.  Patient wheeled out of exam in wheelchair.

Immediately, my arm was in pain. It was like I had been stung by 100 bees. I went back to school but I couldn't use my arm. It lasted two or three days. On second day, I took Ibuprofen and that helped. In the middle of the night (the night after I got my shot, it woke me up with terrible abdominal pains; chills; body aches. By the morning, the abdominal pain was gone - chills, aches and some fatigue. I went and taught school but it got progressively worse and I went home at lunch time. I had a slight fever - it was a high fever for me as I usually run low (96.5). It was about 100.9. I called the clinic the next day (Saturday) because my other symptoms had more or less abated but my left arm was very, very swollen from shoulder to elbow. My coat was too tight on my arm when I tried to put my coat. My arm was cold and my fingers were number. He is the one who told me to take Ibuprofen and elevate my arm and ice it. After the next three days, gradually my swelling went down and my doctor told me to keep using it and keep it moving which I did. Monday, the clinic called to have me talk to the doctor to see about taking the second dose. Doctor said to take the second dose. 2nd dose was much easier for me. My arm symptoms were resolved after about a week.
